a. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[997]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[998]={name_fr=[[Défi: Crise De Noctambulisme]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Unruhige Nächte]],name=[[How I Met Your Marid]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Marids are not known for being nocturnal creatures...yet one of the largest ever observed─Iriz Ima─prefers to feed under cover of night. Its eyes, however, are not suited for seeing in the dark, meaning these evening strolls oft end in the untimely flattening of countless animals, minerals, and Lalafells.]],name_ja=[[夢遊の長老「イリズイマ」]],},[999]={name_fr=[[Les éléments S'éclatent!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Scherbenhaufen]],name=[[Shard To Get]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Throughout the Diadem can be found crystals which have been rendered unstable by the extreme aetherial conditions experienced in the area. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[1000]={name_fr=[[Les éléments S'éclatent!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Scherbenhaufen]],name=[[Shard To Get]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Throughout the Diadem can be found crystals which have been rendered unstable by the extreme aetherial conditions experienced in the area. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[1001]={name_fr=[[Les éléments S'éclatent!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Scherbenhaufen]],name=[[Shard To Get]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Throughout the Diadem can be found crystals which have been rendered unstable by the extreme aetherial conditions experienced in the area. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[1002]={name_fr=[[Les éléments S'éclatent!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Scherbenhaufen]],name=[[Shard To Get]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Throughout the Diadem can be found crystals which have been rendered unstable by the extreme aetherial conditions experienced in the area. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[1003]={name_fr=[[Les éléments S'éclatent!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Scherbenhaufen]],name=[[Shard To Get]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Throughout the Diadem can be found crystals which have been rendered unstable by the extreme aetherial conditions experienced in the area. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[1004]={name_fr=[[Les éléments S'éclatent!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Scherbenhaufen]],name=[[Shard To Get]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Throughout the Diadem can be found crystals which have been rendered unstable by the extreme aetherial conditions experienced in the area. If the volatile energies within these fragments could somehow be harnessed, it could prove an invaluable boon to House Haillenarte.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの回収]],},[1005]={name_fr=[[Nécrophagie Végétale]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wurzel Des Problems]],name=[[Root Of The Problem]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A scavenger, the Bariaua feeds solely on carrion, setting down its roots into corpses and draining them of their remaining humours. What makes this voracious seedkin different is that when hungry, it will not wait to come across a fallen creature, opting rather to slay its own prey in the most violent of fashions.]],name_ja=[[死に花を咲かせよ]],},[1006]={name_fr=[[Nécrophagie Végétale]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wurzel Des Problems]],name=[[Root Of The Problem]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A scavenger, the Bariaua feeds solely on carrion, setting down its roots into corpses and draining them of their remaining humours. What makes this voracious seedkin different is that when hungry, it will not wait to come across a fallen creature, opting rather to slay its own prey in the most violent of fashions.]],name_ja=[[死に花を咲かせよ]],},[1007]={name_fr=[[Nécrophagie Végétale]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wurzel Des Problems]],name=[[Root Of The Problem]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A scavenger, the Bariaua feeds solely on carrion, setting down its roots into corpses and draining them of their remaining humours. What makes this voracious seedkin different is that when hungry, it will not wait to come across a fallen creature, opting rather to slay its own prey in the most violent of fashions.]],name_ja=[[死に花を咲かせよ]],},[1008]={name_fr=[[La Détresse D'un Pirate]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Pirat In Not]],name=[[Nice Pirates]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A gods-fearing, mother-loving, goodly sky pirate has fallen from the rigging of his crew's airship. While fate deemed it not his time, and saw him land safely upon a tuft of crownbrush, fortune was not as impressed and made certain that tuft was located right in the middle of one of the Diadem's most deadly isles. Needless to say, the plucky picaroon might require some assistance.]],name_ja=[[ある空賊の受難]],},[1009]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1010]={name_fr=[[Accros à L'hémoglobine]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Blutsauger]],name=[[Pretty Flies]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Jewel flies earn their name from the bright, ruby-like color of their abdomens─a hue achieved by filling those translucent bellies with the blood of any creature luckless enough to cross the vilekin's path.]],name_ja=[[虫沸きぬ]],},[1011]={name_fr=[[Gorilles Dans Les Ténèbres]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Mitternachtssnack]],name=[[Late-night Snack]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A band of bloodthirsty gigantopithecus have woken from their simian slumber to feed on the sleepy-eyed denizens of the Diadem, and only the bravest of adventurers can provide them with the rude awakening they so deserve.]],name_ja=[[闇夜のギガントピテクス]],},[1012]={name_fr=[[Gorilles Dans Les Ténèbres]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Mitternachtssnack]],name=[[Late-night Snack]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A band of bloodthirsty gigantopithecus have woken from their simian slumber to feed on the sleepy-eyed denizens of the Diadem, and only the bravest of adventurers can provide them with the rude awakening they so deserve.]],name_ja=[[闇夜のギガントピテクス]],},[1013]={name_fr=[[Les Mauvais Garçons]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Einzelgänger]],name=[[Any Which Way]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not all gigantopithecus will hunt in large packs, some choosing to take to the starlit isles of the Diadem in bands of two or three. The clydopithecus (or “clydes”) are one such species, but do not let their adorable name fool you. These beasts are natural-born killers who would tear the heart out of their own mother's breast and gnaw at its sinewy flesh while the life slowly faded from her eyes...if most had not already done so.]],name_ja=[[ダーティファイター]],},[1014]={name_fr=[[Les Mauvais Garçons]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Einzelgänger]],name=[[Any Which Way]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not all gigantopithecus will hunt in large packs, some choosing to take to the starlit isles of the Diadem in bands of two or three. The clydopithecus (or “clydes”) are one such species, but do not let their adorable name fool you. These beasts are natural-born killers who would tear the heart out of their own mother's breast and gnaw at its sinewy flesh while the life slowly faded from her eyes...if most had not already done so.]],name_ja=[[ダーティファイター]],},[1015]={name_fr=[[La Détresse D'un Pirate]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Pirat In Not]],name=[[Nice Pirates]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A gods-fearing, mother-loving, goodly sky pirate has fallen from the rigging of his crew's airship. While fate deemed it not his time, and saw him land safely upon a tuft of crownbrush, fortune was not as impressed and made certain that tuft was located right in the middle of one of the Diadem's most deadly isles. Needless to say, the plucky picaroon might require some assistance.]],name_ja=[[ある空賊の受難]],},[1016]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Vengeance D'un Monarque]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Stoppt Den Souverän]],name=[[Who'll Stop The Sovereign]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Witnessing the wanton slaughter of his entire tribe at the hands of bloodthirsty adventurers has driven the ufiti sovereign into a rage only the sweet ring of cold steel can contain. Send His Royal Excellence to his subjects' side, so that he may rule them from the afterlife.]],name_ja=[[復讐の猿人王「キングウフィティ」]],},[1017]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Vengeance D'un Monarque]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Stoppt Den Souverän]],name=[[Who'll Stop The Sovereign]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Witnessing the wanton slaughter of his entire tribe at the hands of bloodthirsty adventurers has driven the ufiti sovereign into a rage only the sweet ring of cold steel can contain. Send His Royal Excellence to his subjects' side, so that he may rule them from the afterlife.]],name_ja=[[復讐の猿人王「キングウフィティ」]],},[1018]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Vengeance D'un Monarque]],class_level_max=1,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Stoppt Den Souverän]],name=[[Who'll Stop The Sovereign]],class_level=1,help_en=[[Witnessing the wanton slaughter of his entire tribe at the hands of bloodthirsty adventurers has driven the ufiti sovereign into a rage only the sweet ring of cold steel can contain. Send His Royal Excellence to his subjects' side, so that he may rule them from the afterlife.]],name_ja=[[復讐の猿人王「キングウフィティ」]],},[1019]={name_fr=[[Carnivores Des Nuages]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Hungriger Herensugue]],name=[[Hard Of Heren]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Having lived for a thousand years encountering neither Lalafell nor Hyur, the Diadem's herensugues no longer fear mankind and his weapons of war. In their ignorance have they grown bold, leading to many attacks on newly arrived explorers to the islands. It is time they are reintroduced to the pain that kept their ancestors at bay.]],name_ja=[[失われた雲海]],},[1020]={name_fr=[[Périr Le Ventre Vide]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefräßige Kröten]],name=[[Battle Toads]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The relatively small size of each islet in the Diadem can make foraging quite a challenge for the region's wingless inhabitants. It takes the arrival of but a single welkinix, however, to render that challenge an impossibility. Slay the hungry toads before they see the rest of the fauna starve.]],name_ja=[[食べる前に殺す]],},[1021]={name_fr=[[Périr Le Ventre Vide]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefräßige Kröten]],name=[[Battle Toads]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The relatively small size of each islet in the Diadem can make foraging quite a challenge for the region's wingless inhabitants. It takes the arrival of but a single welkinix, however, to render that challenge an impossibility. Slay the hungry toads before they see the rest of the fauna starve.]],name_ja=[[食べる前に殺す]],},[1022]={name_fr=[[Périr Le Ventre Vide]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefräßige Kröten]],name=[[Battle Toads]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The relatively small size of each islet in the Diadem can make foraging quite a challenge for the region's wingless inhabitants. It takes the arrival of but a single welkinix, however, to render that challenge an impossibility. Slay the hungry toads before they see the rest of the fauna starve.]],name_ja=[[食べる前に殺す]],},[1023]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1024]={name_fr=[[Les Séducteurs Ailés]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Die Endymien Sind Los]],name=[[Loose Endymions]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Native to the seamlessly never-ending skies above the Northern Empty, Diadem endymions are a rare sight in the Sea of Clouds. When they do appear, however, it is to the sound of screams─screams of hapless victims being carried off to feed the cloudkin's hungry hatchlings.]],name_ja=[[北洋の人拐い]],},[1025]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Terreur Des Aéronefs]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Kopfgeldjäger]],name=[[Bounty Hunter]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Its recent grounding at the hands of high winds is not the first time the infamous pirate vessel, the Bounty, has been stranded on a Diadem islet. Not but a few moons earlier, an attack by a winged monstrosity known amongst the Sea of Clouds' sky brigands as Hoita nearly tore the airship's hull in two.]],name_ja=[[雲海の撃墜王「ホイタ」]],},[1026]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Terreur Des Aéronefs]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Kopfgeldjäger]],name=[[Bounty Hunter]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Its recent grounding at the hands of high winds is not the first time the infamous pirate vessel, the Bounty, has been stranded on a Diadem islet. Not but a few moons earlier, an attack by a winged monstrosity known amongst the Sea of Clouds' sky brigands as Hoita nearly tore the airship's hull in two.]],name_ja=[[雲海の撃墜王「ホイタ」]],},[1027]={name_fr=[[Circulez, Y A Pas D'ombrelles]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefährliche Jagdgründe]],name=[[Lords Of The Sting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Wasp only in name, the jewel wasp is in fact a gargantuan jellyfish whose ancestors left the seas eons ago to hunt the skies. Little did they know they would be hunting the most dangerous game, and that game always hunts back.]],name_ja=[[ワスプストライク]],},[1028]={name_fr=[[Circulez, Y A Pas D'ombrelles]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefährliche Jagdgründe]],name=[[Lords Of The Sting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Wasp only in name, the jewel wasp is in fact a gargantuan jellyfish whose ancestors left the seas eons ago to hunt the skies. Little did they know they would be hunting the most dangerous game, and that game always hunts back.]],name_ja=[[ワスプストライク]],},[1029]={name_fr=[[Circulez, Y A Pas D'ombrelles]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefährliche Jagdgründe]],name=[[Lords Of The Sting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Wasp only in name, the jewel wasp is in fact a gargantuan jellyfish whose ancestors left the seas eons ago to hunt the skies. Little did they know they would be hunting the most dangerous game, and that game always hunts back.]],name_ja=[[ワスプストライク]],},[1030]={name_fr=[[Circulez, Y A Pas D'ombrelles]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefährliche Jagdgründe]],name=[[Lords Of The Sting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Wasp only in name, the jewel wasp is in fact a gargantuan jellyfish whose ancestors left the seas eons ago to hunt the skies. Little did they know they would be hunting the most dangerous game, and that game always hunts back.]],name_ja=[[ワスプストライク]],},[1031]={name_fr=[[Les Nuages Mangeurs D'hommes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Bewölkt Bis Gefräßig]],name=[[Cloudy With A Chance Of...Thal's Balls]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A storm is coming...in the form of bloated sacks of gelatinous ooze known as cumulonimbi. It is difficult to believe that these alarmingly large sky jellyfish have achieved their staggering girth supping solely on small birds and lizards, recent reports of missing Lalafellin adventurers only fueling the flames of doubt.]],name_ja=[[沸き立つ雲のように]],},[1032]={name_fr=[[Les Nuages Mangeurs D'hommes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Bewölkt Bis Gefräßig]],name=[[Cloudy With A Chance Of...Thal's Balls]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A storm is coming...in the form of bloated sacks of gelatinous ooze known as cumulonimbi. It is difficult to believe that these alarmingly large sky jellyfish have achieved their staggering girth supping solely on small birds and lizards, recent reports of missing Lalafellin adventurers only fueling the flames of doubt.]],name_ja=[[沸き立つ雲のように]],},[1033]={name_fr=[[Les Nuages Mangeurs D'hommes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Bewölkt Bis Gefräßig]],name=[[Cloudy With A Chance Of...Thal's Balls]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A storm is coming...in the form of bloated sacks of gelatinous ooze known as cumulonimbi. It is difficult to believe that these alarmingly large sky jellyfish have achieved their staggering girth supping solely on small birds and lizards, recent reports of missing Lalafellin adventurers only fueling the flames of doubt.]],name_ja=[[沸き立つ雲のように]],},[1034]={name_fr=[[Dévouement Aveugle]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Riskante Unternehmungen]],name=[[Mad Ventures In Retainer-sitting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not content with the paltry pickings his retainer was retrieving from ventures into the Black Shroud, a well-to-do noble recently ordered his humble hireling to the Diadem, forbidding the retainer's return until “treasure worthy of a king” was discovered. All the poor soul discovered, however, was a den of starving sky creatures, and now requires aid in escape.]],name_ja=[[無謀すぎた探索]],},[1035]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Bovin Mythique]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Aufgebrachte Herde]],name=[[Where's The Beef]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A pair of adventurers tired of nibbling on stale tack and moldy cheese have followed their empty bellies to remote wisent grazing grounds, intent on bagging a stray bovine or three to roast over the night's bonfire. What they did not expect was one of the herd to (naturally) take offense.]],name_ja=[[古の巨獣「フォゴットン・ウィセント」]],},[1036]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1037]={name_fr=[[Un Regard Très Perçant]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Gefährliche Augenblicke]],name=[[Sticking Celphies]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Some creatures have an eye for danger, while others simply have eyes that are dangerous. Celphies sit amongst the latter, their gaze deadly enough to stop the hearts of a thousand kings. Literally.]],name_ja=[[魔眼の光]],},[1038]={name_fr=[[Rois Ou Empereurs?]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Blutige Rache]],name=[[Can You Smell The Blood Tonight]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Many summers following the murder of their father─king, nay, emperor of the Diadem─at the paws of their cruel uncle, a pride of cloud lions has returned from exile to reclaim their rightful throne. Unfortunately, their approach thus far has been limited to the indiscriminate slaughter of any and all other wildlife on their homeland isle.]],name_ja=[[大帝か王か]],},[1039]={name_fr=[[Rois Ou Empereurs?]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Blutige Rache]],name=[[Can You Smell The Blood Tonight]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Many summers following the murder of their father─king, nay, emperor of the Diadem─at the paws of their cruel uncle, a pride of cloud lions has returned from exile to reclaim their rightful throne. Unfortunately, their approach thus far has been limited to the indiscriminate slaughter of any and all other wildlife on their homeland isle.]],name_ja=[[大帝か王か]],},[1040]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1041]={name_fr=[[Défi: Efflorescence Fétide]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Luftverschmutzung]],name=[[Hail To The E]],class_level=60,help_en=[[There is something rotten in the air and it is literally leaving visitors to the Diadem with a not-so-fresh feeling. The culprit? A monstrous morbol known as Eccentric Eve. The solution? Her immediate slaying. Freshness has never been simpler.]],name_ja=[[異臭の華族「エクセントリック・イヴ」]],},[1042]={name_fr=[[Entreprise De Désodorisation]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Lunantishees In Der Luft]],name=[[Lunantishee In The Sky]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Extreme levels of ambient aether can not only lead to the increased size and ferocity of a creature, but also to enhanced fertility. Case in point: the Diadem currently finds itself overrun with lunantishee seedlings who, if not dealt with swiftly, will grow into a veritable army of bloodsucking shrubbery.]],name_ja=[[消臭力尽く]],},[1043]={name_fr=[[Entreprise De Désodorisation]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Lunantishees In Der Luft]],name=[[Lunantishee In The Sky]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Extreme levels of ambient aether can not only lead to the increased size and ferocity of a creature, but also to enhanced fertility. Case in point: the Diadem currently finds itself overrun with lunantishee seedlings who, if not dealt with swiftly, will grow into a veritable army of bloodsucking shrubbery.]],name_ja=[[消臭力尽く]],},[1044]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1045]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1046]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1047]={name_fr=[[Experts En Torture]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Peitschenschlag]],name=[[Whiplash]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not many who encounter the dread seedkin Jidras' wicked tangle of whip-like vines survive to tell the tale, while those who have are forever changed. Forever scarred.]],name_ja=[[ムチとムチ]],},[1048]={name_fr=[[Experts En Torture]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Peitschenschlag]],name=[[Whiplash]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not many who encounter the dread seedkin Jidras' wicked tangle of whip-like vines survive to tell the tale, while those who have are forever changed. Forever scarred.]],name_ja=[[ムチとムチ]],},[1049]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1050]={name_fr=[[À Tire D'aile]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Sanfte Gewalt]],name=[[Blood Wings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[For centuries, the pegasi lived in relative peace amongst the forgotten isles of the Diadem. Humanity's recent return to the skies, however, has seen the majestic creatures once again made a target. A few defiant denizens such as the bejeweled pegasus are fighting back, but their indiscriminate rampages are now causing more harm than good.]],name_ja=[[翼をさずける]],},[1051]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1052]={name_fr=[[Les Géants Au Feuillage Touffu]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Mein Freund, Der Baum?]],name=[[NOT THE TREES]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Unnatural concentrations of ambient aether coupled with countless seasons of unobstructed sunlight can be attributed to the freakishly abnormal growth of the Diadem's bilokos─seedkin that if not laid low, will devour any living plant or animal within the reach of their probing roots and branches.]],name_ja=[[根も葉もある噂]],},[1053]={name_fr=[[Les Géants Au Feuillage Touffu]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Mein Freund, Der Baum?]],name=[[NOT THE TREES]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Unnatural concentrations of ambient aether coupled with countless seasons of unobstructed sunlight can be attributed to the freakishly abnormal growth of the Diadem's bilokos─seedkin that if not laid low, will devour any living plant or animal within the reach of their probing roots and branches.]],name_ja=[[根も葉もある噂]],},[1054]={name_fr=[[Les Géants Au Feuillage Touffu]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Mein Freund, Der Baum?]],name=[[NOT THE TREES]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Unnatural concentrations of ambient aether coupled with countless seasons of unobstructed sunlight can be attributed to the freakishly abnormal growth of the Diadem's bilokos─seedkin that if not laid low, will devour any living plant or animal within the reach of their probing roots and branches.]],name_ja=[[根も葉もある噂]],},[1055]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1056]={name_fr=[[Défi: Pêche Au Gros]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Fischersterben]],name=[[Tightropen]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Pteranodons have long been hated amongst fishers, for they are known to greedily devour the selfsame wavekin those men and women depend upon for their livelihoods. Amongst the flying gluttons, there are some which are despised above all others─Ropen, whose mouths are so large, it is said they can scoop a hundred fish in a single dive.]],name_ja=[[ヌシを超える者「ローペン」]],},[1057]={name_fr=[[Migration Interdite]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Unerwünschte Einwanderer]],name=[[I'm The Scatman]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A sun-blotting flock of pteranodons is causing headaches for Ishgardian farmers in the most unexpected of manners. The feces of these prehistoric relics is highly corrosive, and can render a plot of land barren with just a single drop...let alone the hundreds that fall with a single flyby.]],name_ja=[[営巣を阻止せよ]],},[1058]={name_fr=[[Les Yeux Plus Gros Que Le Ventre]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wilde Jagd]],name=[[Wild Hunt]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Known to hunt in pairs─one acting as a decoy, while another attacks from behind─the coelophysis of the Diadem have abandoned their old hunting grounds and taken to the skies above the adventurer campsites and airship landings so that they might stalk their newest delicacy─Lalafell.]],name_ja=[[ワイルドハント]],},[1059]={name_fr=[[Les Yeux Plus Gros Que Le Ventre]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wilde Jagd]],name=[[Wild Hunt]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Known to hunt in pairs─one acting as a decoy, while another attacks from behind─the coelophysis of the Diadem have abandoned their old hunting grounds and taken to the skies above the adventurer campsites and airship landings so that they might stalk their newest delicacy─Lalafell.]],name_ja=[[ワイルドハント]],},[1060]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1061]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1062]={name_fr=[[Dévouement Aveugle]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Riskante Unternehmungen]],name=[[Mad Ventures In Retainer-sitting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not content with the paltry pickings his retainer was retrieving from ventures into the Black Shroud, a well-to-do noble recently ordered his humble hireling to the Diadem, forbidding the retainer's return until “treasure worthy of a king” was discovered. All the poor soul discovered, however, was a den of starving sky creatures, and now requires aid in escape.]],name_ja=[[無謀すぎた探索]],},[1063]={name_fr=[[Le Temps Des Amours]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Milbenbefall]],name=[[(You're) Killing My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A clutch of mite eggs has hatched and now a swarm of ageless mitelings is crawling about the isle consuming aught that moves. Squash the pests before they grow large enough to squash you.]],name_ja=[[バルーニングの季節]],},[1064]={name_fr=[[Le Temps Des Amours]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Milbenbefall]],name=[[(You're) Killing My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A clutch of mite eggs has hatched and now a swarm of ageless mitelings is crawling about the isle consuming aught that moves. Squash the pests before they grow large enough to squash you.]],name_ja=[[バルーニングの季節]],},[1065]={name_fr=[[Le Temps Des Amours]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Milbenbefall]],name=[[(You're) Killing My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A clutch of mite eggs has hatched and now a swarm of ageless mitelings is crawling about the isle consuming aught that moves. Squash the pests before they grow large enough to squash you.]],name_ja=[[バルーニングの季節]],},[1066]={name_fr=[[Le Temps Des Amours]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Milbenbefall]],name=[[(You're) Killing My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A clutch of mite eggs has hatched and now a swarm of ageless mitelings is crawling about the isle consuming aught that moves. Squash the pests before they grow large enough to squash you.]],name_ja=[[バルーニングの季節]],},[1067]={name_fr=[[Lune De Miel Sans Fin]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wo Die Liebe Hinfällt]],name=[[(You're) Having My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[For the vilekin of the Diadem, every season is mating season, and so it is not rare to come across the cacophonous chittering and chirping that is an ageless mite orgy. A female mite can lay upwards of a thousand eggs in a single clutch, so it is left to brave adventurers to see the spawn never take seed.]],name_ja=[[ダイアマイト・ウェディングパーティー]],},[1068]={name_fr=[[La Détresse D'un Pirate]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Pirat In Not]],name=[[Nice Pirates]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A gods-fearing, mother-loving, goodly sky pirate has fallen from the rigging of his crew's airship. While fate deemed it not his time, and saw him land safely upon a tuft of crownbrush, fortune was not as impressed and made certain that tuft was located right in the middle of one of the Diadem's most deadly isles. Needless to say, the plucky picaroon might require some assistance.]],name_ja=[[ある空賊の受難]],},[1069]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1070]={name_fr=[[Les Malheurs Du Célibat]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Liebesfrust]],name=[[(You're Not) Having My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not all diremites are successful in finding a mate, leaving those which don't slightly more agitated than those which do. That agitation oft results in violent outbursts that can last several days until an islet is left a smoldering waste, or until the pent-up sexual tension is fully expelled.]],name_ja=[[ダイアマイト・バチェラーパーティー]],},[1071]={name_fr=[[Les Malheurs Du Célibat]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Liebesfrust]],name=[[(You're Not) Having My Mitelings]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not all diremites are successful in finding a mate, leaving those which don't slightly more agitated than those which do. That agitation oft results in violent outbursts that can last several days until an islet is left a smoldering waste, or until the pent-up sexual tension is fully expelled.]],name_ja=[[ダイアマイト・バチェラーパーティー]],},[1072]={name_fr=[[Nécrophagie Végétale]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Wurzel Des Problems]],name=[[Root Of The Problem]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A scavenger, the Bariaua feeds solely on carrion, setting down its roots into corpses and draining them of their remaining humours. What makes this voracious seedkin different is that when hungry, it will not wait to come across a fallen creature, opting rather to slay its own prey in the most violent of fashions.]],name_ja=[[死に花を咲かせよ]],},[1073]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Félin Ermite]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Einsamer Tiger]],name=[[Good-bye Solo]],class_level=60,help_en=[[It is not known why Gerjis stalks his prey with a lone companion rather than bring the full strength of his pack to the hunt. What is known is that this practice has honed his skills as a predator, making the beast one of the most deadly sabertooth tigers in the whole Diadem.]],name_ja=[[孤高の剣虎「ガージス」]],},[1074]={name_fr=[[Défi: Un Régime à Base De Calories]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Der Große Purpurwurm Nimmersatt]],name=[[Purple Haze]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Purple worms spend nearly the entirety of their lives underground, rising to the surface only once or twice a twelvemoon to feed. It is during these brief forays into the sun that the creatures wreak the most havoc, devouring anything and everything they can before returning to the soil to slowly digest their victims.]],name_ja=[[偏食の地底王「パープルウォーム」]],},[1075]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1076]={name_fr=[[Ça Part En Vrille!]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Achtung, Hornfliegen!]],name=[[Fly By Day]],class_level=60,help_en=[[More than half of airship accidents in the Diadem are attributed to hornflies─drawn to humming of the vessels' engines─becoming caught in propellers. Drive the vile creatures from the Sea of Clouds before further damage can be done.]],name_ja=[[飛ぶ飛空艇を落とす勢い]],},[1077]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1078]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1079]={name_fr=[[Arbres En Folie]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Bäume Im Rausch Des Wahnsinns]],name=[[Forest For The Trees]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The return of the Missing Gem to the Diadem has resulted in further disruption of already erratic ambient aether levels. As a result, species native to the isles such as ageless meliae have grown increasingly violent, posing an immediate threat to scholars and naturalists studying the area.]],name_ja=[[ディアデムの森]],},[1080]={name_fr=[[Arbres En Folie]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Bäume Im Rausch Des Wahnsinns]],name=[[Forest For The Trees]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The return of the Missing Gem to the Diadem has resulted in further disruption of already erratic ambient aether levels. As a result, species native to the isles such as ageless meliae have grown increasingly violent, posing an immediate threat to scholars and naturalists studying the area.]],name_ja=[[ディアデムの森]],},[1081]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1082]={name_fr=[[Carnivores Des Nuages]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Hungriger Herensugue]],name=[[Hard Of Heren]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Having lived for a thousand years encountering neither Lalafell nor Hyur, the Diadem's herensugues no longer fear mankind and his weapons of war. In their ignorance have they grown bold, leading to many attacks on newly arrived explorers to the islands. It is time they are reintroduced to the pain that kept their ancestors at bay.]],name_ja=[[失われた雲海]],},[1083]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1084]={name_fr=[[Empêcheurs De Pêcher En Rond]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Frische Fischer]],name=[[The Other White Meat]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Until recently bottom feeders, many speckled hakulaqs have, of late, developed a taste for more exotic fare─more namely adventurous fishers braving the Diadem in search of their next catch. Volunteers are sought to help frighten off the hakulaqs that all might cast their lines in peace.]],name_ja=[[生まれ出ずる悩み]],},[1085]={name_fr=[[Dévouement Aveugle]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Riskante Unternehmungen]],name=[[Mad Ventures In Retainer-sitting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Not content with the paltry pickings his retainer was retrieving from ventures into the Black Shroud, a well-to-do noble recently ordered his humble hireling to the Diadem, forbidding the retainer's return until “treasure worthy of a king” was discovered. All the poor soul discovered, however, was a den of starving sky creatures, and now requires aid in escape.]],name_ja=[[無謀すぎた探索]],},[1086]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1087]={name_fr=[[Invasion De Sanuwas]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Luftturbulenzen]],name=[[Westwhirled]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Named such for their tendencies to ride the Sea of Clouds' westerly winds, westerly sanuwas are an aggressive cousin to the common sanuwa, and are easily agitated by intruders into their domain. This includes airships, which oft use the westerlies to reduce ceruleum consumption on long voyages.]],name_ja=[[大空のサヌワ]],},[1088]={name_fr=[[Le Bleu De La Mer De Nuages]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Tiefes Blau Sieht Rot]],name=[[Am I Blue]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The Vundu are not ones to show kindness to the sanuwa they capture and tame, employing pain to force their mounts into ultimate submission. Some, however, resist this training and escape back to the skies, though not without their share of scars to the soul. Those known as the Deep Blue are one such example, their hatred of the foul men who laid hands upon them so great, that now they kill without discretion.]],name_ja=[[不幸せの青い雲]],},[1089]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1090]={name_fr=[[Radiations Néfastes]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Elementarer Wahnsinn]],name=[[Excitable Boys]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Aether emitted by unstable elemental crystals is sending even the most docile of creatures into uncontrollable fits of madness. The condition appears to be irreversible, with a swift end the only means of granting these poor souls mercy.]],name_ja=[[放属性シャードの悪影響]],},[1091]={name_fr=[[Sus Aux Constricteurs]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Die Würger Vom Diadem]],name=[[Who's For Dinner]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The serpent-like Uncegila are frighteningly methodical in how they prepare their prey for consumption, first crushing its bones to prevent escape, then delivering a powerful toxin which softens muscle tissue to a paste-like texture, but without killing the victim. The scalekin then devour the quivering mass feetfirst so that they might revel in their prey's final screams.]],name_ja=[[叫び声さえ呑み込まれる]],},[1092]={name_fr=[[Sus Aux Constricteurs]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Die Würger Vom Diadem]],name=[[Who's For Dinner]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The serpent-like Uncegila are frighteningly methodical in how they prepare their prey for consumption, first crushing its bones to prevent escape, then delivering a powerful toxin which softens muscle tissue to a paste-like texture, but without killing the victim. The scalekin then devour the quivering mass feetfirst so that they might revel in their prey's final screams.]],name_ja=[[叫び声さえ呑み込まれる]],},[1093]={name_fr=[[Sus Aux Constricteurs]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Die Würger Vom Diadem]],name=[[Who's For Dinner]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The serpent-like Uncegila are frighteningly methodical in how they prepare their prey for consumption, first crushing its bones to prevent escape, then delivering a powerful toxin which softens muscle tissue to a paste-like texture, but without killing the victim. The scalekin then devour the quivering mass feetfirst so that they might revel in their prey's final screams.]],name_ja=[[叫び声さえ呑み込まれる]],},[1094]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'éventreur De L'azur]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Die Schlitzer Vom Diadem]],name=[[On The Inside]],class_level=60,help_en=[[While much remains unknown about the charybterix, harrowing accounts of the colossal cloudkin using its scimitar-like claws to disembowel its victims have proven enough to convince House Haillenarte that a preemptive strike is the best interest of any and all who plan future forays into the Diadem.]],name_ja=[[美食の凶鳥「ガルピュデス」]],},[1095]={name_fr=[[Les Admiratrices Du Cheval Ailé]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Fabelwesen In Aufruhr]],name=[[Blacker Than The Foulest Witch]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Looking upon these frail creatures, one would not think that unicorns could contain much power. Yet when they are angered, that power oft translates into untold carnage and destruction. Woe betide the man who is fooled by their appearance, for bejeweled unicorns will not hesitate to drive their single majestic horns so deep into your gut, only a spell of temporal reconfiguration might remove them.]],name_ja=[[翼をください]],},[1096]={name_fr=[[Les Admiratrices Du Cheval Ailé]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Fabelwesen In Aufruhr]],name=[[Blacker Than The Foulest Witch]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Looking upon these frail creatures, one would not think that unicorns could contain much power. Yet when they are angered, that power oft translates into untold carnage and destruction. Woe betide the man who is fooled by their appearance, for bejeweled unicorns will not hesitate to drive their single majestic horns so deep into your gut, only a spell of temporal reconfiguration might remove them.]],name_ja=[[翼をください]],},[1097]={name_fr=[[Les Admiratrices Du Cheval Ailé]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Fabelwesen In Aufruhr]],name=[[Blacker Than The Foulest Witch]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Looking upon these frail creatures, one would not think that unicorns could contain much power. Yet when they are angered, that power oft translates into untold carnage and destruction. Woe betide the man who is fooled by their appearance, for bejeweled unicorns will not hesitate to drive their single majestic horns so deep into your gut, only a spell of temporal reconfiguration might remove them.]],name_ja=[[翼をください]],},[1098]={name_fr=[[Défi: Crise De Noctambulisme]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Unruhige Nächte]],name=[[How I Met Your Marid]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Marids are not known for being nocturnal creatures...yet one of the largest ever observed─Iriz Ima─prefers to feed under cover of night. Its eyes, however, are not suited for seeing in the dark, meaning these evening strolls oft end in the untimely flattening of countless animals, minerals, and Lalafells.]],name_ja=[[夢遊の長老「イリズイマ」]],},[1099]={name_fr=[[Entreprise De Désodorisation]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Lunantishees In Der Luft]],name=[[Lunantishee In The Sky]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Extreme levels of ambient aether can not only lead to the increased size and ferocity of a creature, but also to enhanced fertility. Case in point: the Diadem currently finds itself overrun with lunantishee seedlings who, if not dealt with swiftly, will grow into a veritable army of bloodsucking shrubbery.]],name_ja=[[消臭力尽く]],},[1100]={name_fr=[[Accros à L'hémoglobine]],class_level_max=60,patch={number=[[3.55b]],},name_de=[[Blutsauger]],name=[[Pretty Flies]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Jewel flies earn their name from the bright, ruby-like color of their abdomens─a hue achieved by filling those translucent bellies with the blood of any creature luckless enough to cross the vilekin's path.]],name_ja=[[虫沸きぬ]],},[1103]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'étalon Survolté]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Höllenross]],name=[[A Horse Outside]],class_level=70,help_en=[[It is said on a mighty levinbolt doth the warsteed Ixion ride─thunder, the rumbling of his hooves as they pound the very heavens. Ware the coming storm, for hell descendeth.]],name_ja=[[伝説の雷馬「イクシオン」]],},[1104]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'étalon Survolté]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Höllenross]],name=[[A Horse Outside]],class_level=70,help_en=[[It is said on a mighty levinbolt doth the warsteed Ixion ride─thunder, the rumbling of his hooves as they pound the very heavens. Ware the coming storm, for hell descendeth.]],name_ja=[[伝説の雷馬「イクシオン」]],},[1105]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'étalon Survolté]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Höllenross]],name=[[A Horse Outside]],class_level=70,help_en=[[It is said on a mighty levinbolt doth the warsteed Ixion ride─thunder, the rumbling of his hooves as they pound the very heavens. Ware the coming storm, for hell descendeth.]],name_ja=[[伝説の雷馬「イクシオン」]],},[1106]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Renarde Fait Surface]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fuchsige Dame]],name=[[Foxy Lady]],class_level=70,help_en=[[Upon capture by a wicked Hingan onmyoji, the nine-tailed fox spirit slumbering deep within the young maiden Mikuzume awakens. Now, the only way to stop the legendary Tamamo-no-Gozen is with an excessive display of force.]],name_ja=[[九尾の妖狐「玉藻御前」]],},[1107]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Renarde Fait Surface]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fuchsige Dame]],name=[[Foxy Lady]],class_level=70,help_en=[[Upon capture by a wicked Hingan onmyoji, the nine-tailed fox spirit slumbering deep within the young maiden Mikuzume awakens. Now, the only way to stop the legendary Tamamo-no-Gozen is with an excessive display of force.]],name_ja=[[九尾の妖狐「玉藻御前」]],},[1108]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Renarde Fait Surface]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fuchsige Dame]],name=[[Foxy Lady]],class_level=70,help_en=[[Upon capture by a wicked Hingan onmyoji, the nine-tailed fox spirit slumbering deep within the young maiden Mikuzume awakens. Now, the only way to stop the legendary Tamamo-no-Gozen is with an excessive display of force.]],name_ja=[[九尾の妖狐「玉藻御前」]],},[1109]={name_fr=[[Rusera Bien Qui Rusera Le Dernier]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ausgefuchst]],name=[[Outfoxed]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Onmyoji from the Hingan island of Koshu seek to kidnap the young Maiden Mikuzume and subject her to their fell rituals of exorcism. Slay the false priests before the girl is harmed.]],name_ja=[[その名はミクズメ]],},[1110]={name_fr=[[Prétendants Gênants]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kinko In Gefahr]],name=[[Freedom Flies]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Kinko is hotly pursued by several unsavory characters, and fears she will be unable to make it to safety on her own. If only some brave soul would see the roads safe once more.]],name_ja=[[キンコの願い]],},[1111]={name_fr=[[Les Offrandes De Ginko]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ginkos Opfergaben]],name=[[More To Offer]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Hungry Namazu have disturbed the offerings young Ginko has left for a fox who protects the wood. Ginko would gather them herself, but she fears the thieves may still be nearby and seeks a kind soul to search in her stead.]],name_ja=[[ギンコの願い]],},[1112]={name_fr=[[Donner La Réplique Aux Soldats]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Training Für Rekruten]],name=[[Showing The Recruits What For]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The Eorzean Alliance has no shortage of recruits willing to fight under its ivory standard. What it does have a shortage of is skilled fighters to assist in training the mewling privates. Adventurers are sought to bloody some noses.]],name_ja=[[ブートキャンプ：兵卒編]],},[1113]={name_fr=[[Donner La Réplique Aux Sous-officiers]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Training Für Unteroffiziere]],name=[[Showing The Officers What For]],class_level=60,help_en=[[It has been overlong since the Eorzean Alliance has taken part in any serious tactical engagements, and while peace is good for the realm, it dulls both swords and sword arms. Adventurers are sought to serve as the whetstones that will restore the army's edge.]],name_ja=[[ブートキャンプ：下士編]],},[1114]={name_fr=[[Donner La Réplique Aux Officiers]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Training Für Offiziere]],name=[[Showing The Commanders What For]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Without competent commanders, the Eorzean Alliance would be naught more than an army of drunken farmhands and restless mercenaries, incapable of finding their way out of the South Shroud, let alone driving the Garlean invaders from Eorzea. However, to become a competent commander, one must first train against competent foes....or in other words─you.]],name_ja=[[ブートキャンプ：士官編]],},[1115]={name_fr=[[Et Au Milieu Coule Un Ruisseau]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Krokomania]],name=[[Death Beckons]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Timmon Beck serves as the sole source of fresh water for many of the residents of East End...which is why the congregation of recently arrived sarcosuchus cannot be suffered to remain.]],name_ja=[[ワニワニ、ワニっす！]],},[1116]={name_fr=[[Danse Avec Les Ours]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Mit Den Bären Tanzen]],name=[[Unbearable]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Drawn from their dens by the ripe odor of the Eorzean Alliance's latrines, mountain grizzly sightings have become increasingly common as of late, some of these chance encounters leading to serious maiming or even death. The Allied armies seek adventurers to frighten the beasts back into the hills.]],name_ja=[[熊と踊れ]],},[1117]={name_fr=[[Saprias, C'est Fini]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Pflanzen Mit Großem Magen]],name=[[The Secret Life Of Plants]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Gyr Abania has its share of unique highland flora, from prickly thistles, to verdant worts, to man-eating sapria. It suffices to say the latter is not one of which the local smallfolk think that highly.]],name_ja=[[チルドレン・オブ・ザ・サプリア]],},[1118]={name_fr=[[Défi: Bon Ours, Bon œil]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Wiedergänger, Wiederkäuer]],name=[[Dizzy Miss Grizzly]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Flame scouts with the Eorzean Alliance are failing to return to their camps. The culprit, however, does not appear to be the Garleans, but a deadly grizzly sow that has acquired a taste for sweet Lalafellin flesh. As the scouts cannot afford to lose any more of their number, they seek adventurers to cleanse the hills in their stead.]],name_ja=[[混交林の大熊「シャープアイ・グリズリー」]],},[1119]={name_fr=[[Défi: Dopage Alchimique]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Angriff Der Killerkrokos]],name=[[Roid Rage]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Sightings of a gargantuan sarcosuchus colorfully dubbed the “Crocoroid” have residents of the Gyr Abanian Fringes guessing as to its origins, the most popular theory being it swelled to its unnatural size by consuming the discarded bottles of imperial performance-enhancing elixirs.]],name_ja=[[悲劇の変異体「ギガゲイター」]],},[1120]={name_fr=[[Purge Aux Marges]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Aushilfsjäger]],name=[[Keeping The Peace]],class_level=60,help_en=[[When not plotting the overthrow of imperial regime, members of the Ala Mhigan Resistance are tasked with maintaining the peace in the Fringes─ridding the hills and highlands of aggressive fauna whose populations have exploded since the Garlean occupation claimed the lives of many of the region's hunters.]],name_ja=[[辺境パトロール]],},[1121]={name_fr=[[Nouvelle Purge Aux Marges]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Aushilfsjäger Jagen Wieder]],name=[[Keeping More Peace]],class_level=60,help_en=[[When not plotting the overthrow of imperial regime, members of the Ala Mhigan Resistance are tasked with maintaining the peace in the Fringes─ridding the hills and highlands of aggressive fauna whose populations have exploded since the Garlean occupation claimed the lives of many of the region's hunters.]],name_ja=[[続・辺境パトロール]],},[1122]={name_fr=[[Gare Aux Dharas]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Dhara-Derby]],name=[[Double Dhara]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A Resistance fighter separated from his company finds himself surrounded by vengeful elementals and unable to stave off their methodical assault. Race to his aid and earn the gratitude of all Ala Mhigo...or at least his commanding officer.]],name_ja=[[次の岩に続く]],},[1124]={name_fr=[[Gaganas Pique-assiette]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Völlig Gaga]],name=[[Bold This Way]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A pack of young, yet bold, gagana view the sheer cliffs surrounding Rhalgr's Reach as a prime location for their new nests. If allowed to roost on the rocks, it will not be long before the birds are raiding the town's livestock pens. Supplies are already scarce, so a quick solution to this potential problem is sought.]],name_ja=[[チョコボではない]],},[1125]={name_fr=[[Pulsions Déplacées]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fleischeslüste]],name=[[The Morning After]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Swarms of skimmers─some of the vilest of all vilekin─have alighted in the Fringes to mate, and nothing works up an appetite like a frenzied fortnight of fornication. Unfortunately, skimmers have a taste for meat, preferably live, and will attack almost anything and everything that moves, be it livestock, pets, even something as large as a grown Roegadyn.]],name_ja=[[トンボ身重く横たわる]],},[1126]={name_fr=[[Repousser Les Moussemousses]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ohne Moos Mehr Los]],name=[[Thank You For Not Mossling]],class_level=60,help_en=[[While they appear harmless, mosslings are a threat to the fish that share the rivers in which they dwell. If left unchecked, a single colony of these swift-spawning, swift-growing seedkin can cover an entire lake in a matter of moons, blocking sunlight from reaching the riverbed, effectively killing the river's flora and the fauna that feed on it.]],name_ja=[[実はモス生まれ]],},[1127]={name_fr=[[Sus Aux Saillots]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Poststau]],name=[[The Mail Must Get Through]],class_level=61,help_en=[[A storm herald carrying an important communication for his commanders is unable to cross the Velodyna, his way blocked by a school of goosefish. Part the waters and clear the poor man a path to freedom.]],name_ja=[[果しなき河よ我を誘え]],},[1128]={name_fr=[[Au Diable Les Diakkas!]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Dickes Ding]],name=[[Diakka Round]],class_level=61,help_en=[[A company of Eorzean Alliance regulars has been ordered to slay a pack of deadly diakka believed to be the culprits in a disturbing string of missing draught chocobos. Never ones to underestimate their enemy, the company is requesting the assistance of nearby adventurers and is willing to split any spoils earned in the raid.]],name_ja=[[グゥレイト！]],},[1129]={name_fr=[[Défi: Mauvaise Graine]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Saat Des Bösen]],name=[[The Evil Seed]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Legend states that all diakka were born of seeds scattered by Kirnis in her wanderings across Gyr Abania. She continues her journey to this day, spawning more of the deadly seedkin while feeding herself upon the blood of unwary bystanders.]],name_ja=[[樹人の長老「キルニス」]],},[1130]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Colline A Huit Yeux]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ich Glaub, Ich Spinne!]],name=[[The Spiderweb Chronicles]],class_level=61,help_en=[[The larger the spider, the larger the prey it must capture to sate its hunger...and Ankabut is one of the largest spiders to ever be reported in Eorzea. The muffled whimperings heard from the silken sacs on her webs suggest no one in Eorzea is safe.]],name_ja=[[人喰い大蜘蛛「アンカブート」]],},[1131]={name_fr=[[Un Fourmilion Fort Mignon]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ameisenlöwenhunger]],name=[[The Antlion's Share]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Ever seeking to expand their own dominion, aggressor antlions have begun encroaching on M tribe territory. If the trend is allowed to continue, it will not be long before young huntresses start disappearing.]],name_ja=[[アントリオンは大人しいんだ]],},[1132]={name_fr=[[Défi: Un Tyran Au Ban]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Unnahbare]],name=[[Really Don't Keratyrannos]],class_level=67,help_en=[[With their invasion, the Garleans brought with them myriad beasts of war and burden not native to Gyr Abania. Some of these, such as the keratyrannos, have escaped from their masters and now thrive in the highlands where they have no natural predators. Their numbers must be thinned before a disaster strikes.]],name_ja=[[大角の脱走兵「ケラチラノス」]],},[1133]={name_fr=[[Chasse En Hauteur]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Steinsplitterzeit]],name=[[Get Sharp]],class_level=67,help_en=[[As she does every day, a young maid of the M tribe has ventured into the wilds to gather sharp stones for her aunt, the village fletcher. This day, however, the hills are alive with deadly dhara. Is there none who would see the area rid of these creatures so that the youth might be spared her aunt's lashing rod?]],name_ja=[[新石器時代]],},[1134]={name_fr=[[Les Caches Font De La Résistance]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Finger Weg!]],name=[[The Tele-tale Hunt]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Ala Mhigan Resistance fighters have established supply caches across Gyr Abania in preparation for skirmishes with the Empire. Starved creatures of the region such as the saw-toothed teleoceras will raid these crates and devour their contents, and missions to drive off the scalekin are required to maintain supply stocks.]],name_ja=[[所有せざる人々]],},[1135]={name_fr=[[Défi: Martyriser Les Marids]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hiebe Aus Liebe]],name=[[Pop The Trunk]],class_level=67,help_en=[[The Vira keep marids not only for use in battle, but for their rich, fatty milk. The beasts, however, can be quite temperamental, and it is not rare that a beastmaid will lose track of one or two of her herd when grazing them in highland meadows. A good whack or seventeen is usually enough to calm their nerves.]],name_ja=[[暴走の巨象「ランページング・マーリド」]],},[1136]={name_fr=[[Colliers Serrés]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Schmuckraub]],name=[[A Pain In The Neck]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Last night, under the cover of darkness, Ananta of the Qalyana tribe raided a Vira beadmaid's workshop, stealing a goodly amount of jewelry meant for a coming ritual. Having no skill in the art of war, the beadmaid seeks aid in the recovery of her livelihood.]],name_ja=[[血をわけた姉妹]],},[1137]={name_fr=[[Défi: ça Va Barder Pour Berda]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Dicke Berda]],name=[[Flappy Berda]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Once again, warriors of the M tribe hunt the Scourge of the Skies; the Feathered Fiend; White Death. The warriors hunt Berda, and welcome any who might seek to share in their glory.]],name_ja=[[白銀の人拐い「ベルダ」]],},[1138]={name_fr=[[Défi: Sœurs Vengeresses]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Klauen Des Grauens]],name=[[Ananta And Her Sisters]],class_level=67,help_en=[[A party of Ananta battlemaids seek revenge for the wanton slaughter of several of their defenseless sisters at the hands of Jateryu─a bloodthirsty monster that rips open the bellies of its victims with its hooked claws. The battlemaids would not turn away those who might endeavor to aid their quest for ultion.]],name_ja=[[鱗斬りの鉤爪「ジャターユ」]],},[1139]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Fille Du Soleil]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Sonne Des Schreckens]],name=[[Raisin' Hell]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Impressed with your handling of her tribe's unruly marids, the Vira's champion Sunmaid Drisana seeks to ask you one more boon─to cross blades in mock battle.]],name_ja=[[太陽の娘「ドリサナ」]],},[1140]={name_fr=[[Honnis Soient Les Canis]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Wer Ließ Die Hunde Frei?]],name=[[Yes, This Is Dogs]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Trained from birth to kill on command, the Garlean Empire's canis pugnaces are feared across the realm. Now, reports are that several of the murdering machines have escaped their captors' fetters and are roaming the Fringes, taking out their aggressions on any moving thing in sight.]],name_ja=[[野良犬]],},[1141]={name_fr=[[La Chasse Gardée Des M]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Stolze Kriegerinnen]],name=[[M Bop]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Archers of the M tribe will not suffer the likes of the Qalyana defiling their sacred hunting lands and are petitioning local adventurers to join them in driving off the sly serpentesses.]],name_ja=[[高い村の女]],},[1142]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'eau, Elle Aime ça]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Mädchen Mit Dem Nassen Haar]],name=[[Wet]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Her name meaning literally “wet woman,” Nure-onna is a malevolent spirit who has taken the form of a beautiful young maiden to lure men into her lair. Here, she flays her victims and feeds them to her pets─loyal gyuki demons who do her every bidding.]],name_ja=[[牛鬼の使い「ヌレオンナ」]],},[1143]={name_fr=[[De Corvée Avec Les Bucorves]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Stinkevögel]],name=[[Clean Bill Of Health]],class_level=62,help_en=[[The hornbills that nest on the myriad islets of the Ruby Sea can prove a breathtaking sight from afar; however, up close, their rookeries are laden with foul-smelling bird lime that causes all manner of maladies when taken into the lungs. The Confederacy will pay handsomely for the removal of these winged pests.]],name_ja=[[迷惑な落とし物]],},[1144]={name_fr=[[Défi: à Tout Jamais]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Für Immer Und Immer]],name=[[Quoth The Raven]],class_level=63,help_en=[[Ruby Sea alehouses are abuzz with tales of an ill-omened bird sailors have dubbed “Forevermore.” If the stories are to be believed, the cloudkin will alight upon a ship's prow and repeat the words “forever and ever” several times over before flying off to the horizon. The following morning, if even a third of the crew remains, they can consider themselves fortunate. Now, that bird is said to be frightfully near...]],name_ja=[[不吉な怪鳥「イツマデ」]],},[1145]={name_fr=[[Défi: On Craint Gedan]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Langfinger Lang]],name=[[Lay Of The Lang]],class_level=63,help_en=[[A lone wolf is terrorizing the village of Isari, stealing livestock and defiling rice paddies. There are even rumors that he whispers in children's ears as they sleep, telling them to ignore their chores and disobey their elders. It is high time someone did something about Kuimu Lang, and that someone is you!]],name_ja=[[漁村の脅威「ケイボクロウ」]],},[1146]={name_fr=[[Vidange Pour Les Verts]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Pool-Party]],name=[[Pool Party]],class_level=62,help_en=[[A school of testy tatsunoko have congregated in the Blue Kojin's sunbathing pools and threaten to drive the peaceful beastmen from their daily basks. Drive the wavekin back into the seas whence they came so that the Blue might warm their shells once again.]],name_ja=[[青い紅玉]],},[1147]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Crabe Marche Sous La Tête]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schnipp-schnapp, Kopf Ab!]],name=[[Soak Up The Sun]],class_level=62,help_en=[[From Kugane's back alleys to her bathhouses, dark rumors spread like blood from the neck of a decapitated criminal. The rumor? That the decapitated head of Mishirushi─a fallen warrior executed for murder─has come back to life to continue its killing ways, slicing up innocent maidens with its crab-like claws. Crab-like claws?]],name_ja=[[敗戦の大兜「ミシルシ」]],},[1148]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Philosophie D'Agni]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Agnis Philosophie]],name=[[Agni's Philosophy]],class_level=62,help_en=[[When not devouring the very lava that oozes forth from Hells' Lid, the fire-aspected anala, Agni, is devouring those foolish enough to approach her demesne. Have you the mettle to quell her flames of rage?]],name_ja=[[炎纏う者「アグニ」]],},[1149]={name_fr=[[Bons Comptes à OK Corail]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Rubinrote Korallen]],name=[[The Coral High Ground]],class_level=62,help_en=[[The Ruby Tithe is not the only manner in which pirates of the Confederacy line their coffers with coin. Some lower-ranking members are tasked with gathering beached coral for sale to Kugane's lapidaries. One such enterprising young pirate is offering a percentage of her cut to all who aid her in her search.]],name_ja=[[赤い珊瑚礁]],},[1150]={name_fr=[[Privés De Banquet]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Überfall Auf Die Korallentafeln]],name=[[The Big Banquet Theory]],class_level=62,help_en=[[The Coral Banquet─haven for the Confederacy─is under attack by a company of Red Kojin who show little interest in negotiation. While not believed a threat to the outpost, every moment spent fending off the assailants is a moment not spent fighting the Confederacy's bigger battles.]],name_ja=[[紅甲羅関所破り]],},[1151]={name_fr=[[Des Serpents Dans Les îlots]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kriecher Aus Der Tiefe]],name=[[Uncivil Serpents]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Apparently not satisfied with being relegated to the briny deep, a brood of slithering spotted sea serpents has set its sights on the sun-dried hills and dales of the Ruby Sea's islands, and are prepared to take them with venom-fueled force.]],name_ja=[[海からの侵略生物]],},[1152]={name_fr=[[Lâcher De Raies]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kampfrochen]],name=[[Ray Band]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Seeking to bring a swift end to their never-ending conflict with the Confederacy, the Red Kojin have led a school of poisonous striped rays into pirate territory, overwhelming many of the sentries stationed on the island's outskirts. Protect the survivors and hold off the intruders until reinforcements arrive.]],name_ja=[[紅甲羅あばれ凧]],},[1153]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Princesse Aux Longues Dents]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Prinzessin Yahiro]],name=[[Princess, Princess]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Nagori, Confederacy pirate, has sworn to exact revenge on the flying shark that swooped down and ate her younger brother while he was strapping his boots. This is easier said than done, for the culprit is none other Yahiro─feared princess of the razor-toothed wavekin.]],name_ja=[[飛鮫の姫君「ヤヒロノワニ」]],},[1154]={name_fr=[[Athlétiques Bibao]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Unglücksraben]],name=[[Kill The Messenger]],class_level=63,help_en=[[Bi fang─a predatory bird native to Yanxia─are widely thought of as harbingers of ill fortune, so when an entire flock arrives from the west, one might understand why they would be so willing to pay good coin to see the birds slain and their bodies tossed to the tides.]],name_ja=[[渇きの海]],},[1155]={name_fr=[[Pêche à La Bombe]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Bomber Oder Fisch?]],name=[[The F-bomb]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Eorzean scholars of the void have yet to determine whether or not the Ruby Sea's bombfish are in fact voidsent like their western counterparts, or simply a unique aquatic species native to Hydaelyn. Any and all observations on habitat and behavior in battle will be paid for in good coin.]],name_ja=[[指きり拳万]],},[1156]={name_fr=[[L'écarlate Scélérate]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kriegsherrin Der Rotpanzer]],name=[[Raise The Red Flag]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Amahire the Redmost commands a party of Kojin raiders and striped rays in a surprise assault on Sakazuki. Drive the invaders back to the Ruby Sea before they do any real damage.]],name_ja=[[紅甲羅海を渡る]],},[1157]={name_fr=[[Mollusque à Brusquer]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Magische Muscheln]],name=[[Double Dream Clams]],class_level=63,help_en=[[The Ruby Sea shellfish known as yumemi will sometimes remain dormant on the ocean floor for several moons, siphoning aether from thermal fissures and storing it inside its shell. Once enough mana has been accumulated, the mollusk will rise from the depths and emerge to hunt on land, killing indiscriminately with its primitive magicks.]],name_ja=[[夢の丘]],},[1158]={name_fr=[[Les Horreurs De L'aurore]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Vom Nordwind Gebracht]],name=[[There Be Dragonflies]],class_level=63,help_en=[[A plague of dawnborn dragonflies comes from the north and west threatening the flora and fauna of the Ruby Sea's isolated islands. The coastal villages are banding together to drive back the vilekin and would not turn away an adventurer with a mind to help.]],name_ja=[[北風のうしろ]],},[1159]={name_fr=[[Défi: Prendre Le Clandestin Par Les Cornes]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ein Berg Von Einem Gyuki]],name=[[Bilge-hold Jin]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Confederate pirates were in for the surprise of their lives when a stowaway was discovered in the bilges after a recent raid to the coasts of Koshu. This was no ordinary stowaway, however, but a massive bull demon known to Hingans as Jinrinki. How it came to hide in the ship, none know, but now that it is out, it must be put down.]],name_ja=[[無礼なる牛鬼「ジンリンキ」]],},[1160]={name_fr=[[Le Butin, ça Va, ça Vient]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Des Wahnsinns Fette Beute]],name=[[Days Of Plunder]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Red Kojin have risen from the seas to plunder the Confederacy of plunder it rightfully plundered. To protect this plunder from future plundering, the pirates have assigned a man to guard the hidden plunder caches. The problem is, this guard is the greenest of green recruits, and fares little chance of emerging from the coming encounter with his head.]],name_ja=[[されど修羅ゆく君は]],},[1161]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Chevalier D'écailles]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Junge, Junge, Diese Rotpanzer]],name=[[Forever Younglier]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Insistent on plundering the pirates of their hard-plundered plunder, the Red Kojin have sent in one of their finest warriors, a thick-shelled veteran known as Katabira the Younglier, who also happens to be a master of ninjutsu.]],name_ja=[[激流の亀忍者「十代のカタビラ」]],},[1162]={name_fr=[[Reprendre N'est Pas Voler]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schatzsuche]],name=[[Treasure Island]],class_level=63,help_en=[[Several curiosities have been stolen from altars tended to by the Blue Kojin. The perpetrators─unsurprisingly a band of Red Kojin─still lurk nearby, and the Blues are seeking help in locating the thieves and taking back what is rightfully theirs...using any means necessary.]],name_ja=[[紅甲羅千両首]],},[1163]={name_fr=[[Maille à Partir]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Jetzt Gibt's Tote]],name=[[Sailor Marooned]],class_level=63,help_en=[[Some say shiranui are the restless spirits of shipwrecked sailors. Others, the signal lamps of draconian deities. What they all agree on is that when even one appears─let alone an entire congregation─lives will be lost.]],name_ja=[[知らぬが仏]],},[1164]={name_fr=[[Les Vils Requins]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Haie Im Anflug]],name=[[Jumping The Shark]],class_level=62,help_en=[[When a school of flying sharks have devoured all the life in one corner of the sea yet remain unsated, they turn their fins to the shallows, where they hunt everything from birds to tigers...and even the occasional Lalafell!]],name_ja=[[スカイシャークズ]],},[1165]={name_fr=[[Défi: Fais Tes Prières, Sogenbi]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Sogenbis Sühne]],name=[[Red Cliff]],class_level=63,help_en=[[Cast from the cliffs for stealing relics from his temple, the priest Sogenbi's body perished on the rocks below, but his evil spirit remained, bound to the corporeal realm. Now he wanders the Ruby Sea, preying on the souls of the innocent...and the not-so-innocent, when no innocent are available.]],name_ja=[[不徳の僧侶「ソウゲンビ」]],},[1166]={name_fr=[[Avant Qu'il Ne Soit Taureau Tard]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Rette Die Fische - Und Die Fischer!]],name=[[Ranging Bull]],class_level=62,help_en=[[The bull-like demons known as gyuki are known to prefer the colder northern climes, yet will ever so often journey south to the Ruby Sea to feed when food is scarce. A herd approaches now, and local fishers fear that if measures are not taken, the seas will soon empty.]],name_ja=[[牛鬼泥棒]],},[1167]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Samouraï Vagabond]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Samurai Aus Den Bergen]],name=[[Another One Bites The Dust]],class_level=62,help_en=[[After moons of training in his secluded mountain hovel, Senban Oneblade has journeyed down to the Ruby Sea in search of worthy opponents with whom he can test his newly acquired skills.]],name_ja=[[兵法修行人「一刀のセンバン」]],},[1168]={name_fr=[[Vagabond Contre Chasseur]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Eingekesselt]],name=[[Turtle Power]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Hearing that Senban Oneblade has come down from his mountain hovel, a Red Kojin warrior seeks to steal the hermit's one blade─Kame-wari─waiting until he is overcome with fatigue from one of his challenges before launching their attack. Defend the injured Senban from his assailants so that he may live to train another day.]],name_ja=[[紅甲羅逆手斬り]],},[1170]={name_fr=[[Casse-toi Et Marche En Crabe]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Einfach Mal Treiben Lassen]],name=[[Crab Mentality]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Unkiu hunt by riding ocean currents, preserving energy until they have spotted their prey which, for these unfussy eaters with perpetually empty bellies, is just about anything with meat on its bones.]],name_ja=[[兜割]],},[1171]={name_fr=[[Enrayer Les Raies Rayées]],class_level_max=67,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[12½ Rochen]],name=[[Independence Ray]],class_level=63,help_en=[[The striped ray is one of the Ruby Sea's most deadly predators and almost impossible to tame, so it is a testament to the Red Kojin's tenacity...or stubbornness that they endeavor to do so. However, it is not rare to find that one or more of the wavekin have again escaped their captors' nets, even more frenzied than they were before.]],name_ja=[[海の貴婦人]],},[1172]={name_fr=[[Défi: Amocher Les Daimyo]],class_level_max=66,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fürstlicher Appetit]],name=[[Never Say Daimyo]],class_level=62,help_en=[[Yumemi never stop growing, adding to their bulk with every turn of the moon. Those few which have survived the longest are dubbed “daimyo,” and must literally eat constantly to sustain life...much to the chagrin of fishers who are left with empty seas in the yumemi's wake.]],name_ja=[[夢見る大名「ダイミョウユメミ」]],},[1173]={name_fr=[[Le Qiqirn Végétarien]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Freundliche Nager Von Nebenan]],name=[[A New Leaf]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Mimiroon Leafgrinder's companions have been ratnapped, and the kindly Qiqirn finds himself unable to free them on his own. Mimiroon seeks an equally kind adventurer to serve as his sword while he uses his sensitive snout to suss out the location of his soul-shrews.]],name_ja=[[完全菜食主義]],},[1174]={name_fr=[[Le Top De La Fraîcheur]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Unfreundliche Nager Von Nebenan]],name=[[Salad Days]],class_level=60,help_en=[[It appears Mimiroon Leafgrinder and his herbivorous helpers are not as opposed to consuming meat as his own name would suggest...and it appears you are on the menu.]],name_ja=[[精進料理]],},[1175]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Qiqirn Sournois Au Ventre Vide]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Genug Genagt!]],name=[[A Bone To Pick]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The Bonecruncher formerly known as Leafgrinder has proven himself a right scoundrel, and this affront cannot well be forgiven lest he endeavor to repeat the ruse on another unsuspecting rube.]],name_ja=[[空腹の詐欺師「肉食のミミルン」]],},[1176]={name_fr=[[Qu'il Est Long, Le Chemin Du Retour]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Und Täglich Grüßt Das Nagetier]],name=[[And The Bandits Played On]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Residents of Ala Gannha tend not to stray too far from the protective walls of their humble hamlet, for when they do, a Qiqirn bandit is usually there waiting to steal their clothes, their coin, or worse...their lives. Escorts are thoroughly appreciated, and handsomely paid.]],name_ja=[[死ぬのは奴らだ]],},[1177]={name_fr=[[Repas à La Ferme]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Feldmäuse In Groß]],name=[[Of Mice And Men]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Ever the greedy gluttons, a band of Qiqirn cutthroats have descended the Peaks to raid local farmsteads of their bountiful harvest. The smallfolk cannot defend their land armed with but spades and hoes. An adventurer, however, may have more success.]],name_ja=[[血の収穫]],},[1178]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Cauchemar Des Paysans]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gefräßiges Chapuli]],name=[[Churlish Chapuli]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Those who have chosen to make their homes on the unforgiving slopes of the Peaks have done well to coax whatever plant they can from the barren soil. Which is why it is all the more disheartening to see those hard-earned crops torn from the fields by gluttonous vilekin─vilekin like the dread chapuli.]],name_ja=[[農民の悪夢「スパーナル・チャプリ」]],},[1179]={name_fr=[[Pic De Pollution]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Einfach Nur Zum Heulen]],name=[[Down With The Sickness]],class_level=60,help_en=[[The lichyard behind Ala Gannha is full to bursting with the freshly buried bodies of those to have recently succumbed to the Weeping Cough─an affliction that induces hacking fits so terrible, that it makes the victim shed tears. The cause of this illness? The scales shed by the giant moth-like bloodgliders that fly over the village at night. If they were to be slain, the people might be saved.]],name_ja=[[ブラッドミュージック]],},[1180]={name_fr=[[Tenir Tête Au Fléau]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kinder Der Plage]],name=[[Child's Plague]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Ala Mhigan legend tells of an ancient Gyr Abanian king whose pride angered the gods and brought upon his fertile land a plague of winged insects that devoured all grass and trees, leaving the desolate Peaks that remain to this day. The vilekin chapulis are believed by some to be the remnants of that plague.]],name_ja=[[チャプリの移民]],},[1181]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Bûcheron Silencieux]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Mit Dem Kopf Durch Den Wald]],name=[[You Don't Know Jack]],class_level=61,help_en=[[While some beetles will scour forests for entire days in search of wounded trees from which they can sip sticky sweet sap, one particular vilekin simply uses its head. Literally. Lumber Jack is notorious for violently butting against solemn sentinels until they topple so he may suck the life from the exposed trunk. If let to continue, there might not be a single tree left in all the Peaks come winter.]],name_ja=[[沈黙の木樵「ランバージャック」]],},[1182]={name_fr=[[Défi: Etain, La Reine Des Fluturinis]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Lila Lethargie]],name=[[Winging It]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Wings of orange herald the morn
Wings of white herald the night
Wings of gold herald the cold
Wings of purple...are filled with deadly poison what will melt your organs from the inside. Always take care when dealing with wings of purple, and Etain─queen of the fluturini─has a pair of the purplest.]],name_ja=[[魔蝶の王妃「エーディン」]],},[1184]={name_fr=[[Rats Dégriffés]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Waffentruhe Zu Waffenruhe]],name=[[Beat Boxes]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Qiqirn cutthroats are preparing an assault on Ala Gannha and have consolidated their weaponry in conveniently labeled lockboxes conveniently located not far from the humble hamlet. If someone were to destroy these boxes and their contents, the bumbling bandits would be oh, so inconvenienced.]],name_ja=[[アラガーナ防衛線]],},[1185]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Barbier Diabolique]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ein Flotter Schnitt]],name=[[Barbershoppe]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Despite his title, the Brutal Barber is by no means a licensed practitioner of medicine, and any limbs entrusted to his care will most likely be lopped off, regardless of whether or not they require medical treatment.]],name_ja=[[伝説の藪医者「ブルータルバーバー」]],},[1186]={name_fr=[[Empennage De Qualité]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Federn Lassen]],name=[[Fletching Returns]],class_level=68,help_en=[[Seeing an opportunity to profit off the coming conflict, an independent sutler is collecting griffin feathers that he plans on crafting into arrows─arrows that he will sell at a premium to the Ala Mhigan Resistance, the griffin being the symbol of their fallen city-state. The sutler will gladly purchase any feathers you happen upon, as well.]],name_ja=[[グリフィンの物語]],},[1187]={name_fr=[[Éclosion Lépidoptère]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Alter Falter]],name=[[Days Of Fluturini Past]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Adult fluturini will lay hundreds of eggs each day, and while some of these eggs will be consumed by predators, their sheer number ensures that many will survive to hatch...grow...and kill. Seek out and swat the swarms which threaten to wreak havoc in the Peaks.]],name_ja=[[胡蝶の夢]],},[1188]={name_fr=[[Défi: Quitte Ou Double]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Klotz, Der Aus Der Hölle Kam]],name=[[Diceman Cometh]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Pious men say that gambling is a sin and that those who lose themselves in games of trump and dice will be damned to the seven hells where their spirits will become corporeal manifestations of their worldly vice. As ridiculous as this may sound, the mere existence of the fell Crapaud makes a good case in favor of the pious.]],name_ja=[[凶悪なる骰子「クラッブス」]],},[1189]={name_fr=[[Un Appétit D'ogre]],class_level_max=65,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gern Auch Gammelfleisch]],name=[[Stuck In The Muud]],class_level=61,help_en=[[Muud suuds have been cursed by the gods with an insatiable hunger that drives the creatures to madness. When not devouring flesh, be it rotting or fresh, they are searching for flesh...be it rotting or fresh.]],name_ja=[[拷問者の影]],},[1190]={name_fr=[[La Hantise Des Hyurgoths]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Wenn Der Große Hunger Kommt]],name=[[Eat Big Or Go Home]],class_level=68,help_en=[[To sate their appetites, highland erucas do not bother with “smaller” prey such as rabbits, tigers, and chocobos. Qiqirn merchants, Ananta battlemaids, Roegadyn mercenaries. These are what the vilekin crave.]],name_ja=[[ハイランダー悪魔の虫]],},[1191]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'immonde Chien Féroce]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Zum Fressen Gern]],name=[[Love Me, Tindalos]],class_level=68,help_en=[[They say that dogs are a man's best friend. Tindalos, on the other hand, is no friend to man...or woman, for that matter. Tindalos is merely hungry, and would rather devour any and all who dare cross his path than make their humble acquaintance.]],name_ja=[[不浄なる獣「ティンダロス」]],},[1193]={name_fr=[[L'appel De L'aventure]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Plötzliches Heimweh]],name=[[Home On The Range]],class_level=68,help_en=[[Upset that his father insisted he take up the plow over the sword, a young boy of Rustrock decided he would leave the safety of his family's farmstead behind and join the Ala Mhigan Resistance. What he failed to take into consideration were all the ravenous beasts that would be waiting for him in-between, and now desperately needs an escort home.]],name_ja=[[エルカ探検隊の大冒険]],},[1194]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'affreux Humbaba]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hunba, Hunba, Hunba, Tätärä!]],name=[[Rattle And Humbaba]],class_level=68,help_en=[[Life in the Peaks can be downright difficult, but the people of the J tribe somehow manage with what little they have. Yet, when what little they have is constantly being stolen by a heartless brute by the name of Humbaba, that is simply salt in their wounds. The J seek a champion that might ease their pain.]],name_ja=[[豪腕の襲撃者「フンババ」]],},[1195]={name_fr=[[Prière Exaucée]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Vergissmeinnicht]],name=[[Forget-me-not]],class_level=68,help_en=[[A warrior of Coldhearth who journeyed to the Bull's Bath for his weekly dip forgot his sword by the pond, and now finds himself assailed by kongamato with no way to defend himself. Assist the man home where he may procure a second sword to help him retrieve his first.]],name_ja=[[待ってたんだ！]],},[1196]={name_fr=[[Oiseau De Proie]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Zum Greifen Nah]],name=[[The Day Of The Griffins]],class_level=68,help_en=[[The founders of Ala Mhigo chose the griffin for their kingdom's standard for its strength, ferocity, cunning, and endurance─all traits that make the winged beastkin one of the most deadly creatures you will ever meet, if not the last creature you ever meet.]],name_ja=[[血より生まれし]],},[1197]={name_fr=[[Défi: Autant En Emporte Le Ventus]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hyperventilation]],name=[[Venting]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Anila are dreadful creatures whose incessant gyrations birth hot, sand-filled storms that ruin crops and send caravans tumbling from canyon-tops. Ventus is by far the worst of this breed, grown fat on the flesh of its lesser brothers.]],name_ja=[[暴風の元凶「ウェントゥス」]],},[1198]={name_fr=[[Défi: Casse-cou S'abstenir]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hals- Und Genickbruch]],name=[[Breakneck]],class_level=68,help_en=[[When the King of Ruin fell, his head executioner, refusing to be subjected to the same cold justice he dealt his entire life, slit his own throat. Unable to bear the loss, the executioner's pet beast─Neckbreaker─took to the Peaks, where he has been continuing his kind master's work ever since, much to the chagrin of the region's innocent residents.]],name_ja=[[執行人の家系「ネックブリーカー」]],},[1199]={name_fr=[[Tourbillon De Poussière]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Staub, Staub, überall Staub!]],name=[[Attack Of The Groans]],class_level=60,help_en=[[When an anila spins, it kicks up copious amounts of dust─dust that is coarse and rough and irritating and gets literally everywhere. Every anila slain, a dervish averted. Every dervish averted, a pair of knickers free of sand's itchy burden.]],name_ja=[[風と共に来たる]],},[1200]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Pyromane Des Pics]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Feuer Ist Für Motten Nichts]],name=[[Moth To A Flame]],class_level=60,help_en=[[To hear the smallfolk of the Peaks tell it, one in three of every home set to flame is done so by the notorious pyromantic, Ignamoth. While these numbers may be inflated, that does not change the fact that a massive fire-starting vilekin is flying loose about the countryside, and should probably be put down. Quickly.]],name_ja=[[優雅なる放火魔「イグナモス」]],},[1201]={name_fr=[[Abnégation Héroïque]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Definitionssache]],name=[[Resist, Die, Repeat]],class_level=60,help_en=[[A Resistance fighter is putting up his best resistance against a flock of fighting chapuli who are resisting all his attempts to break free from the fighting. Are you so cold as to resist the call to aid in his fight?]],name_ja=[[チャプリの勇敢]],},[1202]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Veuf Vengeur]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fünf Ist Trümpf]],name=[[Slaughterwife-five]],class_level=68,help_en=[[Nenaunir is said to have taken five wives─five wives he all loved with equal measure. When those wives were hunted and slain, he swore revenge against all mankind, and will not stop killing until he, himself, is killed.]],name_ja=[[復讐の寡男「ネナウニル」]],},[1203]={name_fr=[[Le Don Du Repos éternel]],class_level_max=64,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Und Was Sich Reimt, Ist Bhut]],name=[[Das Bhoot]],class_level=60,help_en=[[Their rage binding them to the corporeal realm, the spirits of young Ala Mhigans slain at the hands of Garlean invaders roam the Peaks seeking vengeance even now, more than twenty summers removed from the fall of their kingdom. Release the spirits from this world that they might finally find respite in the beyond.]],name_ja=[[エクソシスト]],},[1204]={name_fr=[[Défi: Métamorphose En Suspens]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fünf Nahrhafte Jahre]],name=[[5-year Energy]],class_level=68,help_en=[[Their large bodies and relatively bright coloring make erucas easy targets for hungry predators large enough not to become prey themselves. There lives, however, one worm so full of vim and vigor that it has eluded capture for five whole summers, allowing it to swell to its current gargantuan girth. It should be noted that vim and vigor came from consuming the local citizenry.]],name_ja=[[幸運なる大食漢「エナジェティック・エルカ」]],},[1205]={name_fr=[[Guerrière De La Tribu Des J]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Grauen Panteras]],name=[[Mouth For Water]],class_level=68,help_en=[[Try as she might, J'najaq Sunflare is struggling to fend off the bloodthirsty panteras that threaten to maim and maul the J tribe maid who has come to the river to gather water. The warrioress sees you approach and sends a pleading glance.]],name_ja=[[ジャ族の戦士]],},[1207]={name_fr=[[Défi: Alarme Fatale]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Brennpunkt Reifstein]],name=[[The Magitek Is Back]],class_level=68,help_en=[[The Lethal Weapon was meant to give the Empire the upper hand against the armies of Eorzea, yet it proved too difficult to control for even the most experienced of magitek operators. The test model created was decommissioned and stored in a lonely warehouse where it was to await dismantling...until it came to life! Destroy the contraption before it lays waste to the entire front!]],name_ja=[[暴走最終兵器「リーサルウェポン」]],},[1208]={name_fr=[[Détrousseurs Koja]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gyogun Im Pech]],name=[[A Tisket, A Tasket]],class_level=64,help_en=[[A humble Namazu by the name of Gyogun has returned home with a catch that will feed his family for days. Unfortunately, the aroma has garnered the attention of a pack of starving koja intent on turning Gyogun's pain into their gain. Protect Gyogun's full-to-bursting baskets so that his spawn need not go hungry tonight.]],name_ja=[[ギョグンの不運]],},[1209]={name_fr=[[Détrousseurs Namazu]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gyogun Im Unglück]],name=[[A Fish To Fry]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Not a moment after Gyogun's daring escape from the koja's prying paws is the poor Namazu surrounded by a school of his tribe's most rotten─the thugs intent on claiming the catch for their own. Gyogun's full-to-bursting baskets are once again in need of protecting, lest his spawn suffer the night with empty bellies.]],name_ja=[[ギョグンの非運]],},[1210]={name_fr=[[Défi: Gyogun Le Garde-pêche]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gyogun Dreht Durch]],name=[[Falling Drown]],class_level=64,help_en=[[The day's events have transformed the mild-mannered Gyogun into a quivering mass of uncontrollable rage. If left to his own devices, the Namazu will most certainly cause unintended harm to others, if not himself. Attempts at rational discussion have been met with baleful stares and low growling. It appears the only way to soothe the savage fish may be through a few well-placed wallops to the head.]],name_ja=[[痺れる激情「豊漁のギョグン」]],},[1211]={name_fr=[[Le Lupin Est Un Loup Pour Le Lupin]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Wolfskriege]],name=[[Scared Straightheart]],class_level=67,help_en=[[While indeed many of the Lupin can prove difficult or even deadly, Gaei Straightheart is an honorable youth with a passion to right wrongs and defend those unable to defend themselves. That said, his passion for do-goodery oft runs him afoul with less-than-savory characters─characters not unlike those surrounding him now...]],name_ja=[[人狼：紅い足跡]],},[1212]={name_fr=[[La Meute Sanguinaire]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Wolfskriege II]],name=[[Wolves Of A Feather]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Alerted to their brother's plight, several of Gaei's pack have hurried to his side to assist in driving back those who would do him harm. Join the Lupin in their fight to defend Gaei.]],name_ja=[[人狼：鋼鉄の猟犬]],},[1213]={name_fr=[[Défi: Wakizashi Le Chasseur De Lames]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Wolfskriege: Letzte Jagd]],name=[[Goodwill Hunterling]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Seeing their fortunes falter with the arrival of Gaei's pack, Straightheart's assailants summon forth their final weapon─an ill-reputed Kojin mercenary known as Wakizashi the Hunterling. Put him down, and the rest may finally admit defeat.]],name_ja=[[紅い甲羅「刀狩のワキザシ」]],},[1214]={name_fr=[[Prise De Bec]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schnäbelrasseln]],name=[[Stay Of Eggsecution]],class_level=64,help_en=[[A murder of violent bi fang have alighted amidst hornbill nesting grounds, sending the already excited cloudkin into a frenzy for fear that their nests will be seized and their eggs stolen. Join the hornbills in driving off the invaders and protecting their unborn young.]],name_ja=[[ベニツノ凶鳥狩り]],},[1215]={name_fr=[[Défi: Ovipare Ovivore]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Nesträuber]],name=[[Get Ready For A Nu Wave]],class_level=64,help_en=[[The bi fang driven back to the mountains, the hornbills returned to their nests content...until through the quiet fields of rice they saw slither a serpent with eyes like rubies and a mouth like a dying sun. Nu Wa─bane of the Gensui Chain─had come for its favorite prey: eggs.]],name_ja=[[鯰狙いの大蛇「ニュ・ワー」]],},[1216]={name_fr=[[Les Dents Du Ciel]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Wenn Haie Hunger Haben]],name=[[Deep Red Sea]],class_level=64,help_en=[[In search of prey, flying sharks native to the Ruby Sea have swum upstream into the brackish mouth of the One River to feed on anything and everything that might call the delta home─including those fish already caught in local Doman fishers' nets.]],name_ja=[[戦慄の血飛沫]],},[1217]={name_fr=[[Défi: Il Court, Il Court, Le Furet]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Blutdurstige Wiesel]],name=[[To Catch A Weasel]],class_level=64,help_en=[[While the term “weasel” conjures images of small, scrawny rodents, Doman weasels are anything but small or scrawny. In addition, the massive beastkin have a remarkably acute sense of smell, and can detect the scent of blood from over a malm distant. Drawn by your slaughter of the flying sharks, the wickedest of weasels─Fuchikari─has descended to the One River and threatens to wreak utter havoc.]],name_ja=[[扶持の狩手「フチカリ」]],},[1218]={name_fr=[[Éclosion Explosive]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Skandal, Sie Schnäbeln Wieder!]],name=[[Footing The Bills]],class_level=64,help_en=[[River hornbills, while mostly harmless, can prove quite testy come mating season─males unable to find mates giving to frequent bouts of violence against any man or animal unfortunate enough to be nearby. For the residents of quiet Namai, it is during this time that their little corner of heaven cut from the Gensui Chain turns into hell.]],name_ja=[[遮二無二]],},[1219]={name_fr=[[Tigres Grégaires]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Auge Des Tigers]],name=[[Tiger Need]],class_level=64,help_en=[[It is rare for a Yanxian tiger to attack someone without provocation unless it is extremely hungry. Unfortunately, Yanxian tigers require twice their weight in raw meat every day, meaning they are almost always hungry.]],name_ja=[[虎のゆりかご]],},[1220]={name_fr=[[Topographie Rizicole]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Nimmersatten Raupen]],name=[[Leave The Meters Running]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Every planting season, the rice farmers of Namai must deal with all manner of pests and blights which threaten to spoil entire crops. One of the biggest of those, by far, are plagues of geometers─voracious vilekin which can devour an entire paddy of seedlings in a matter of bells, leaving naught but caustic droppings which poison the land.]],name_ja=[[怪しい虫]],},[1221]={name_fr=[[Régulation De Population]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hörner Stutzen]],name=[[The Long And Rhino Road]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Unlike other vilekin whose insatiable appetites pose a threat to Namai's secluded rice paddies, rhino beetles are feared and despised for a completely different reason─their stampedes. Rhino beetles will descend upon the village in herds, flattening anything in their path as they search for the sweet tree sap upon which they feed.]],name_ja=[[狩って兜の緒を締めよ]],},[1222]={name_fr=[[La Meute De L'ombre]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Ganze Affenbande Brüllt]],name=[[Raze The Red Lantern]],class_level=64,help_en=[[During the Garlean invasion of Doma, large swathes of Yanxian wilderness were razed, leaving nothing but the charred remains of once lush forests. The fauna that once called that land home has been forced to roam deep into the realm of man in search of food. The violent exchanges that have erupted as a result have left many a family grieving the loss of a loved one.]],name_ja=[[猿の大軍団]],},[1223]={name_fr=[[Racines Ambulantes]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Lange Hände, Lange Finger]],name=[[Long Hands, Long Fingers]],class_level=64,help_en=[[The Far East is home to countless fantastical creatures unknown to those raised in the west. One such example is the “tenaga” or “longhands”─wooden gargoyles born of corrupted aether that has permeated the roots of certain trees. Though different in many ways, their lust for murder, however, very much mirrors that of their Eorzean counterparts.]],name_ja=[[テナガおじさん]],},[1224]={name_fr=[[Les écumeurs De Rizières]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Sonst Setzlingst Was!]],name=[[Rice And Shine]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Namazu wildlings have once again invaded Namai; though not in search of food or coin, but intent on stealing the village's stock of rice seedlings. If not retrieved, the farmers will miss their planting window, and risk losing their entire crop─a disaster that would leave more than one family hungry come winter.]],name_ja=[[稲生物怪録]],},[1225]={name_fr=[[La Recette De L'omelette]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Bauernfrühstück]],name=[[In One Basket]],class_level=64,help_en=[[The rice farmers of Namai have few qualms with the river hornbills that make their nests alongside the village paddies...as long as the cloudkin's populations are kept under control. This requires periodical checks of their nests and the removal of eggs in cases where there are more than one. One farmhand seeks the aid of adventurers to help him complete this surprisingly dangerous task.]],name_ja=[[ベニツノの卵は誰のもの]],},[1226]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Lueur Des Champs]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Heiß, Heiß, Baby]],name=[[Tsurubebi Snugly]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Minobi are brilliant fire-aspected specters who dwell in the valleys nestled 'twixt the Gensui Chain's ebon peaks. While most are solitary creatures, legend has that one─Tsurubebi─has grown fat supping on the very souls of its brethren, and that the power gained has rendered it quite mad.]],name_ja=[[田園の怪火「ツルベビ」]],},[1227]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Comédien Pourpre]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fürsorgliche Mutter]],name=[[Motherly Love]],class_level=64,help_en=[[From their birth, Doman children are told terrifying tales of Songsi, a crimson cloudkin that lures boys and girls from their homes by calling out in an eerily woman-like voice. Once their victims have strayed far enough from safety, the monster will swoop down and snatch up the children, then carry them back to its mountaintop nest where it will tear them limb from limb for its own fledglings.]],name_ja=[[紅色の役者「ショウシ」]],},[1228]={name_fr=[[Défi: Pollution Environnementale]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Umweltsünden]],name=[[Killer Apsaras]],class_level=64,help_en=[[The foul discharge of the Garlean invaders' warmachina not only spoils the land, preventing crops from growing, but corrupts the very aether that flows through her. Elemental creatures that draw energy from this aether are driven to madness, such as the once peaceful Apsaras─now feared by all who call Doma home.]],name_ja=[[汚水の精「アプサラス」]],},[1229]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Chien Noir De Yanxia]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hundsgemein]],name=[[Linquan Continental]],class_level=64,help_en=[[If there is one thing the continent of Othard is not lacking, it is colorful tales of legendary monster dogs who stalk the shadows in search of virgin maids and succulent babes. Linquan is one such monster dog, and yes, everything you have heard about the abomination is true. Especially the part about the succulent babes.]],name_ja=[[青黒の妖犬「リンチュアン」]],},[1230]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'éclipse à Plumes]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Schrecken Der Sonnenanbeter]],name=[[This Is A Da, This Is A Peng]],class_level=64,help_en=[[Legend says that Dapeng─a massive cloudkin several times larger than its bi fang cousins─has a wingspan so large that it supposedly blots out the sun. However, if you are close enough to Dapeng that you can no longer see the sun, then chances are the last thing you are worried about is seeing the sun.]],name_ja=[[日食の巨鳥「タイホウ」]],},[1231]={name_fr=[[Défi: Qui épouvante L'épouvantail?]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Albtraumhafte Scheuche]],name=[[Oneblade Wonder]],class_level=64,help_en=[[A Hingan swordsman wandering through Doma on a journey of enlightenment and self-betterment has stumbled across a scarecrow possessed of a shikigami─a minor spirit─believed no longer under the control of its conjurer. Though he insists he is fine, it is obvious the swordsman is in over his head, and will require assistance if he is to escape this horror with his life.]],name_ja=[[狂える案山子「クエビコ」]],},[1232]={name_fr=[[Les Malandrins Du Goûter]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Niederträchtige Namazuo]],name=[[Mister Whiskers]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Namazu bandits are the slipperiest of thieves, both literally and figuratively, and while for the most part they prove bumbling and incompetent, their sheer numbers make them a real threat for solitary travelers. Adventurers experienced in the disciplines of war or magic are sought to deal with the nuisance.]],name_ja=[[ナマズオどうしよう]],},[1233]={name_fr=[[Les Lupins Solitaires]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gefallene Wölfe]],name=[[Crying Wolves]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Lupin who have, for one reason or another, been driven from their packs will oft end up members of small independent parties which seek revenge on those they believe wrong them─which, in their mind, ends up being everyone but themselves.]],name_ja=[[人狼の野武士]],},[1234]={name_fr=[[Renforts Intrépides]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Grimmige Blicke]],name=[[Mada's Ilk]],class_level=67,help_en=[[A pack of mada have journeyed far south from their native Azim Steppe to hunt and have settled on a location far too close for the comfort of those stationed in the House of the Fierce. Join the would-be liberators in this test of strength and bravery.]],name_ja=[[烈士伝]],},[1235]={name_fr=[[Tora! Tora! Tora!]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Getrübter Badespaß]],name=[[Tora Tora Tora]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Fearing the flying sharks of the One River, several Namazu have come to Prism Lake to bathe. To their surprise, they find themselves out of the frypan yet into the fire when a clowder of rainbow tigers spots them on the shore and decides it is time for supper...]],name_ja=[[トラ、トラ、トラ！]],},[1236]={name_fr=[[Défi: Ragoh Perd La Tête]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Von Allen Guten Geistern Verlassen]],name=[[Ragoh To Extremes]],class_level=67,help_en=[[When the master of a summoned shikigami such as Ragoh dies before the spirit can be returned to its plane of origin, its mind slowly succumbs to madness, unable to anchor itself in reality. This is when the spirits are their most dangerous, and if not dealt with swiftly, bring about great tragedy.]],name_ja=[[巨頭の暴君「ラゴウ」]],},[1237]={name_fr=[[Défi: Avis D'éviction]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Tiger Troll Dich]],name=[[Très Bian]],class_level=67,help_en=[[The ruins of the once-majestic Doman enclave are all but abandoned by man, leaving room for a new leader, one that rules with an iron hand...er, paw─Bian. Yet now, the regent grows bold, leading his hunting parties of rainbow tigers deep into liberator camps. Perhaps it is nigh time the king is declawed and dethroned.]],name_ja=[[精強なる老虎「ヘイカン」]],},[1238]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Géant De Fer]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Naseweise Namazuo]],name=[[Curiosity Killed The Catfish]],class_level=67,help_en=[[Instead of leaving the giant contraption alone, several Namazu who stumbled upon an abandoned automaton of unknown origin felt compelled to poke it with sticks, ultimately awakening the metal beast now compelled to vaporize everything that moves.]],name_ja=[[逆心の巨兵「キドウ丸」]],},[1239]={name_fr=[[Chiens De Bonne Herpe]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Auf Den Hund Gekommen]],name=[[The Virgin Homicides]],class_level=64,help_en=[[More of Doma's many legendary demon dogs have appeared to terrorize the land's young virgins who, it appears, demon dogs prefer over young harlots, old virgins, and old harlots. Think of the virgins. The young ones.]],name_ja=[[妖犬伝説]],},[1240]={name_fr=[[Cosmologie Hingashienne: Le Shikigami Kiyofusa]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Geister, Die Sie Riefen]],name=[[Dead To Rites: Kiyofusa]],class_level=64,help_en=[[An onmyoji from the Hingan isle of Koshu has sailed to Yanxia to perform unthinkable rites banned in his homeland. It is through blood sacrifice, that the wicked priest has summoned forth a restless spirit─a shikigami─and granted it a body in which it might now sow terror into the hearts of all Domans.]],name_ja=[[陰陽師：清房ノ巻]],},[1241]={name_fr=[[Cosmologie Hingashienne: Le Shikigami Koja]],class_level_max=68,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Geister, Die Er Rief]],name=[[Dead To Rites: Koja]],class_level=64,help_en=[[An onmyoji from the Hingan isle of Koshu has sailed to Yanxia to perform unthinkable rites banned in his homeland. It is through blood sacrifice, that the wicked priest has summoned forth a restless spirit─a shikigami─and granted it a body in which it might now sow terror into the hearts of all Domans.]],name_ja=[[陰陽師：鼓子ノ巻]],},[1242]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Proie Vengeresse]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gejagte Jäger]],name=[[Don't You Mean Kirata]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Some tribes of the steppe require of their youths the slaying of a ferocious beast, such as a baras, to prove their journey to adulthood is complete. One clever baras─a monster known as Kirata─has learned to use these rites of passage as an opportunity to hunt for the tender flesh of the unbloodied.]],name_ja=[[狩人を狩る者「キラタ」]],},[1243]={name_fr=[[Défi: Silence, ça Pousse!]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Blutrünstiger Narantsetseg]],name=[[The State Of Reunion]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Reunion is the one place on the Azim Steppe where the myriad Xaela tribes can put aside their differences and come together as one to trade and to revel in relative peace. The terrible beast Narantsetseg, however, sees it merely as a place where prey gathers. Warriors of the Qestir have gathered to slay the creature and ask the help of any willing and able. That is, the tribe would ask if they ever talked.]],name_ja=[[再会を阻む者「ナランツェツェグ」]],},[1244]={name_fr=[[Défi: Refroidir Le Vent Glaçant]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kalter Nordwind]],name=[[Cold Comes The Wind]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Khatayin warriors led by Qatun Coldwind have descended from the north seeking a fight...and it happens the cave-dwelling Uyagir are the first in line. Join the Uyagir in protecting their homes and earn the respect of their peaceful tribe.]],name_ja=[[北部の女傑「寒風のクァトゥン」]],},[1245]={name_fr=[[Chasse Privée]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Rivalisierende Jäger]],name=[[A Tall Order]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Towering hunters of the Olkund tribe have ventured into Oroniri territory to poach the land of its abundant fauna. Join warriors of the Oronir in protecting their sacred hunting grounds by driving off the Olkundi in the only way they will understand─with brute force.]],name_ja=[[密猟者たち]],},[1246]={name_fr=[[Défi: Buffet à Volonté]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Wüstenvogel]],name=[[Duck And Cover]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Xaela tribes across the Azim Steppe tell tales of a horrible giant duck that flies from beyond the Nhaama Desert every autumn to sup on the flesh of man. The word for “giant duck” sounds far more imposing in their native languages.]],name_ja=[[大空の誘拐者「サムパティ」]],},[1247]={name_fr=[[Défi: Taratata]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Lautes Heulen In Der Steppe]],name=[[Feel The Noise]],class_level=66,help_en=[[At nightfall, a hush falls over the Azim Steppe, welcoming the Dusk Mother back to her throne that she may reign in blissful silence. In blissful silence if the manzasiri Rudra was not rousing the dead each and every evening with its incessant howling. A great boon is promised to he or she who quiets the veldt.]],name_ja=[[叫声の野人「ルドラ」]],},[1248]={name_fr=[[Défi: Tondeuse Sur Pattes]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Grasverderber]],name=[[Get Out The Vochu]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Without its sea of emerald grass, the Azim Steppe would be but a desert...which is why the foul Vochu must be slain before its draining of the land's lifeblood leaves the region in ruin.]],name_ja=[[除草の達人「ブオチュー」]],},[1249]={name_fr=[[Vombrellules En Surnombre]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schlanke Brummer]],name=[[Buzzkill]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Buzzflies do much more than simply buzz. They sting, they bite, and they eat...and eat, and eat, and eat. And what is worse, their preferred fare is the living flesh of the steppe's beastkin, which they douse in digestive juices so that they might sip the liquefied muscle from their victims' bones.]],name_ja=[[ザ・フライ]],},[1250]={name_fr=[[Sur Un Malentendu...]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Uneinsichtiger Falschspieler]],name=[[A Good Day To Die]],class_level=65,help_en=[[For several moons, Bukidai the Wandering River worked Reunion's gambling tents, swindling many a hunter of their hard-earned pelts. Upon the discovery of his dishonest deeds, the man was rightly cast out of the city, yet the stubborn Bukidai feels he was wronged and now seeks to re-enter the city, by means of violence if necessary.]],name_ja=[[沈黙の制裁]],},[1251]={name_fr=[[On Ne Marchande Pas Avec Un Mammouth]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Mammutaufgabe]],name=[[Wooly Boys]],class_level=65,help_en=[[A Qestiri merchant finds himself on the wrong side of a mammoth herd and seeks assistance on removing the herd from between him and where he needs to be.]],name_ja=[[マンモスと暮らすには]],},[1252]={name_fr=[[Bon, Des Baras]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Jagdrudel]],name=[[Razing The Baras]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Baras are some of the Azim Steppe's most feared predators. Not only are they lightning fast and possessed of razor-sharp claws, but they tend to hunt in groups, making them all the more deadly.]],name_ja=[[草原の赤いイナズマ]],},[1253]={name_fr=[[En Emportant Le Duvet Qui était Son Nid Un Beau Matin]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gefräßiges Federvieh]],name=[[The Fangover]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Driven from Yanxia by helpful adventurers, a flock of bi fang have flown north over the Gensui Chain and into the steppe in search of fresh meat. Fearing their livestock may be on the menu, several of the Xaela tribes seek helpful adventurers to herd the cloudkin back to Yanxia.]],name_ja=[[鳥]],},[1254]={name_fr=[[Défi: Contrôle Des Naissances]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Königin Der Brummer]],name=[[Hat's Off]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Her belly nigh-bursting with eggs, queen of the steppe buzzflies─Hatan─searches for place to lay her clutch. Knowing the chaos even a single buzzfly can herald, the immediate extermination of Her Royal Vileness is less a suggestion, and more a necessity for survival.]],name_ja=[[多産の王妃「ステップ・ハタン」]],},[1255]={name_fr=[[On Ne Peut Pas Tromper Mille Fois Une Personne]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Übers Ohr Gehauen]],name=[[Rock For Food]],class_level=65,help_en=[[A Xaela youth cozened by Ura miners descended from the mountains to trade their ore for food seeks retribution. While he may be in the right, he is also severely outnumbered, and seeks one brave of heart to stand at his side in his quest for justice.]],name_ja=[[時には懺悔を]],},[1256]={name_fr=[[Le Bol D'air Pue]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Unerträglicher Gestank]],name=[[Purbol Reign]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Something is in the air, and it is far from the sweet, alluring scent of roses or honey. The sound you hear is the collective gags of a thousand thousand Xaela as they suffer the ill winds born of the burps and belches of the dread purbol.]],name_ja=[[プルプルプル]],},[1257]={name_fr=[[Défi: Cinq Troncs Et Feuillages Par Jour]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Keimling Undsiig]],name=[[Eat You Better]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Undsiig roams the steppe devouring the land's rare trees, mayhap believing that their gnarled flesh will strengthen his own. Whether or not this is true, the gluttonous seedkin must be stopped before not a single sentinel stands.]],name_ja=[[飢えたる根人「フン・ウンデス」]],},[1258]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'indomptable]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Eine Ausgeburt Der Steppe]],name=[[Man To Mangas]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Many of the Azim Steppe's dzos have been domesticated by the many Xaela tribes which rely on their hair, milk, and meat for survival. Tsaagan Mangas is one exception, this aggressive specimen grown large thanks to years of cunning. If one were to take this legend down, she would be seen as a hero among heroes.]],name_ja=[[大草原の怪物「マンガス」]],},[1259]={name_fr=[[Défi: Gergei A La Bougeotte]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[In Stein Gemeißelt]],name=[[Not Just A Tribute]],class_level=65,help_en=[[A statue honoring legendary hero Gergei the Great has unexpectedly come to life, and appears to be just as hale as the warrior who it is said once slew an army of weasels with a single swing of his mighty fist.]],name_ja=[[石人の英雄「ゲルゲイ・チョロー」]],},[1260]={name_fr=[[Il Va Y Avoir Du Sport]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Gefährliche Kröten]],name=[[Good Day To Mate]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Matamata are irritable enough year-round, but come mating season, the scalekin are downright unruly. It has even been suggested that the only thing keeping the steppe from being overrun is that the number of newborns are offset by the number of matamata killed by in-fighting between males in heat. Well, that and the hunting parties of adventurers.]],name_ja=[[亀がアウラに言ったこと]],},[1261]={name_fr=[[Qui Veut La Peau De Mon Hainag?]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Lebensgrundlage Der Olkund]],name=[[Killing Dzo]],class_level=65,help_en=[[A young nomad was leading her family's prized dzo back from a nearby watering hole when a pack of starved gedan emerged from the steppe's tall grass, intent on making the livestock its next victim. The girl seeks aid before the hounds close in.]],name_ja=[[家路につく牛飼いの少女]],},[1262]={name_fr=[[Désert Brûlant]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Feuriger Wüstenwind]],name=[[Burn After Evening]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Hot winds blowing from the south have carried several fire sprites from the Nhaama Desert and into the Azim Steppe. If not dealt with immediately, the entire grassland might be in flames before next nightfall.]],name_ja=[[赤い砂漠]],},[1263]={name_fr=[[Manzasiri, Y Es-tu?]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Fressen Und Gefressen Werden]],name=[[Hey, Manzasiri]],class_level=66,help_en=[[The nomadic tribes of the Azim Steppe must face many hardships as they journey the grasslands in search of land where their livestock might graze─none of those greater than the wicked manzasiri. These formidable beasts are most feared by the Xaela for their tendency to kill not for food, but simply for the sheer enjoyment of it.]],name_ja=[[野獣狩り]],},[1264]={name_fr=[[Défi: Repousser Du Gulo]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Khan Der Gulo Gulo]],name=[[Khan Artist]],class_level=66,help_en=[[Deadly steppe weasels known as gulo gulo are on the move, scampering and scurrying from camp to camp terrorizing livestock and their poor shepherds. With each taste of blood, the rodents grow frenzied, and only the pacification of their fearsome leader─Gulo Khan─might send them back to the hills, tails 'twixt their stubby legs.]],name_ja=[[残虐な覇者「グログロハーン」]],},[1265]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'odeur De La Tortue Verte]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Stinker Stinkhaut]],name=[[Hook, Like, And Stinker]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Assigning names to the myriad creatures of the Azim Steppe has never been a strong suit of the Xaela nomads, so when a tribe came across a malcontent matamata whose skin reeked of the funk of forty-thousand summers, they named it Stinkskin and immediately put a bounty on its noisome nob.]],name_ja=[[這い寄る悪臭「スティンクスキン」]],},[1266]={name_fr=[[Les Analas Se Mettent Au Vert]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Steppe In Flammen]],name=[[Fired]],class_level=66,help_en=[[The one thing that the nomadic Xaela truly fear (other than being slain or captured by aggressive tribes, being captured then eaten by aggressive beasts, and being eaten by aggressive beasts that steal you from a tribe that has captured you), are steppe that can see an entire herd of livestock starve. For this reason, flame-spouting anala can be afforded little in the way of tolerance.]],name_ja=[[野火]],},[1267]={name_fr=[[Défi: Attention, Passage De Mammouths]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Tödliche Hauer]],name=[[Wham, Bam, Thank You, Mammoth]],class_level=65,help_en=[[When mammoths stampede, not much remains in their wake save blood and dust. When led by the mightiest mammoth of all─Mahishasura─that wake can stretch from one end of the steppe to the other. While the tribes may succeed in slowing the wooly beast, it will take the strength and wile of an adventurer to stop him.]],name_ja=[[長牙の圧殺者「マヒシャスラ」]],},[1268]={name_fr=[[Bataille Pour Les Pâturages Du Milieu]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Pflanzenwelt Schlägt Zurück]],name=[[More Than You Chaochu]],class_level=65,help_en=[[The ochu of Eorzea are but dainty daisies in a meadow when compared to the horrors that are the chaochu─their reach so long that if you can see one, you are already too close. Their teeth so sharp, they can slice through ten-ilm steel like a hot iron through ice. Their breath so bad, it can make a man retch all the way across the Ruby Sea. (Alright, that last one may be an exaggeration, but you get the picture.)]],name_ja=[[優しき雑草の反抗]],},[1269]={name_fr=[[Je T'ai Volé Ton Lait]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[In Der Gewalt Der Buduga]],name=[[They Shall Not Want]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Seeking to strengthen their tribe, a band of Budugan warriors have kidnapped a shepherd of the Mol. Will anyone heed his cries?]],name_ja=[[つかのまの悪夢]],},[1270]={name_fr=[[Berger, Un Métier à Risque]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schutz Vor Den Buduga]],name=[[A Walk Through The Valley]],class_level=65,help_en=[[The shepherd is free from his bonds, but fight remains in the Budugan warriors who would see the youth theirs. Drive back the attackers as your new charge navigates the steppe back to the safety of his tribe's village, Mol Iloh.]],name_ja=[[よみがえる悪夢]],},[1271]={name_fr=[[Défi: Où Es-tu, Mani Manikantha?]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Auf Bardams Probe Gestellt]],name=[[Live For The Mettle]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Having emerged from Bardam's Mettle seemingly having proved his mettle, the doubly proud and triply vicious Manikantha seeks to sate a hunger grown large on the proving grounds. The Mol, sensing that the beast's hunger may take him to their livestock pens─or worse, their yurts─have sent warriors to slay him, and seek any aid a nearby adventurer might provide.]],name_ja=[[覇道の帰還者「マニカンタ」]],},[1272]={name_fr=[[Sélection Semi-naturelle]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Dämpfer Am Seldsee]],name=[[Off Their Yabby]],class_level=69,help_en=[[The sweet, succulent flesh of yabby tails was so adored by Ala Mhigan royalty, that an area of Loch Seld was cordoned off to farm the crustaceans. With the fall of the city-state, the nets quickly fell into disrepair, allowing the wavekin to escape into the lake proper where they have since multiplied unchecked. Help is sought by local fishers in thinning the yabby population.]],name_ja=[[ロッホ・セル湖畔の戦い]],},[1273]={name_fr=[[Défi: Ce Pataud De Crapaud]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Forsche Frosch]],name=[[Foul Bachelor Frogamander]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Little scares the Empire, years of conditioning rendering their soldiers rocks in the face of even the worst of odds. For some reason, however, not even the hardest of Garlean commanders will muster the courage to stand against the bloated abomination that is Frogamander─archimandrite of the abaddons.]],name_ja=[[不動の大蝦蟇「フロガマンダー」]],},[1274]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Belle Est La Bête]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Die Tragische Jungfrau]],name=[[Old Bucket Of Boruta]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Locals say that only after a young maiden─grief-stricken upon learning that her father had promised her to an evil baron─flung herself from Lochwatch did the rogue rafflesia Boruta begin terrorizing the region. Is the seedkin a manifestation of the girl's anguish, or simply a creature invigorated after supping on the girl's spilled humours? Does it even matter? The flower is eating children!]],name_ja=[[悲恋の乙女「ボルータ」]],},[1275]={name_fr=[[Pollution Sonore]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Froschbelästigung]],name=[[Dusk Till Abaddon]],class_level=69,help_en=[[It has been three nights since the fishers of Loch Seld last slept. Three nights of incessant croaking so loud, even a turnip in each ear cannot muffle the noise. Croaking so thunderous, spines tingle and urns tumble from their boards above the kitchen. The culprits? Abaddons. The solution? Steel.]],name_ja=[[騒音アバドン]],},[1276]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Sent-bon De La Sangsue]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Duft Des Todes]],name=[[The Smell That Leeched Her Heart]],class_level=69,help_en=[[The aroma leech is an efficient hunter, emitting a soft, pleasant scent that attracts many a skipping maiden, afield in search of pretty flowers to knit wreaths and garlands. Yet what those maidens find is naught but a slow, agonizing death at the sucking maw of a bloodthirsty monster.]],name_ja=[[死の芳香「アロマ・リーチ」]],},[1277]={name_fr=[[Défi: Ciel, Mon Sosie]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Zwei Hohe Berge]],name=[[Tall Tale]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Ala Mhigan resident Tall Mountain woke this morning with the city watch at his door claiming he was under arrest for crimes he has no recollection of committing. At the same time, a burly, wan-faced Hellsguard appeared in the Lochs, covered from head to toe with blood that did not appear to be his own. Could this impostor be the true culprit?]],name_ja=[[白色大顔面「トール・マウンテン」]],},[1278]={name_fr=[[Défi: Célibataire Enforci]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Kurrea, Der Abgrundtief Hässliche]],name=[[Taking Kurrea Business]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Come mating season while all other ninki nankas were caught in the throes of passionless rutting, Kurrea simply used the opportunity to feed, growing larger...and larger...and larger, until he was nigh abursting. Now that there is naught left to consume, he has taken to his second favorite pastime─the slaughter of innocents.]],name_ja=[[不人気の怪物「クレア」]],},[1279]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'arbre Carnivore]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Wurzelbehandlung Mit Blutverlust]],name=[[Dude, Where's My Karya]],class_level=69,help_en=[[As is the case with most ambulatory trees, warm, freshly drained lifeblood is what ancient Karya craves, the seedkin trapping its victims in its tangle of roots and branches, and keeping them alive with its own sickly sweet fruit so that it might sup slowly.]],name_ja=[[虚ろなる老木「カリュアー」]],},[1280]={name_fr=[[Défi: Il Faut L'imaginer Heureux]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Der Lehmmann-Schock]],name=[[Sisyphus Cooling]],class_level=69,help_en=[[A heretofore unseen golem has been sighted pushing boulders about nearby caves─caves from whose very walls the beast is believed to have been formed. By whom and for what purpose this lithic monster was given life is unknown, but those who have seen their kin torn in two by the massive creature's claws will tell you this: Sisyphus must die.]],name_ja=[[剥落せし岩獣「シーシュポス」]],},[1281]={name_fr=[[Défi: Les Minots Ont Tort]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Brust Oder Keule]],name=[[Minotaurs On My Mind]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Until a fortnight ago, many Ala Mhigans believed minotaurs to be naught more than stories told to keep children from exploring the deadly caves surrounding the Lochs. When children began disappearing, people still blamed the caves, boarding their entrances so as to discourage the curious. When a giant minotaur was seen carrying a young Lalafell into the night, however, people finally knew Asterion was real.]],name_ja=[[雷光の魔牛「アステリオス」]],},[1282]={name_fr=[[Sans Rancune]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[999 Stufen In Den Tod]],name=[[Dive In]],class_level=69,help_en=[[So paranoid did the King of Ruin become in his final days, that not a day would go by where servants, aides, cooks─even kin─were not sent plummeting from the Divine Audience to their dooms. It is said that to this day, the Lochs are haunted by restless specters, bound to this realm by their wrath.]],name_ja=[[断頭台への招待]],},[1283]={name_fr=[[Anilas Ah Ah Ah]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Versalzene Ruinen]],name=[[Pounding Salt]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Since the Garlean invasion, the Firkins have remained in a state of disrepair─all attempts at rebuilding hampered not only by the occasional salvo of imperial cannon fire, but by the untamed salt anilas who have taken up residence in the crumbling buildings.]],name_ja=[[過ぎ去りし日々の風]],},[1284]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'ami Asthme]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Hauch Des Todes]],name=[[Lalla Land]],class_level=69,help_en=[[An ill wind blows down from the hills rendering all caught in its path...well, ill. The cause of this unnatural plague? Lalla Mira─a malevolent spirit of wind whose breath carries with it the very air of death.]],name_ja=[[死病の運び手「ラッラミラ」]],},[1285]={name_fr=[[Une Dérouillée Pour Les Soblyns]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schaltet Den Schmerz An, Schnell]],name=[[When It Pains It Pours]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Long have scholars postulated as to why soblyns are so aggressive compared to their lowland cousins. One theory is that the corrosion to their metallic carapaces caused by the accumulation of salt crystals causes the creatures constant pain, leaving them in a perpetual state of frenzy. Or, it could simply be they are evil, evil beings.]],name_ja=[[死を告げる白虫]],},[1286]={name_fr=[[Défi: Soblyn-minal]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Verrückt Vor Schmerz]],name=[[Sob Story]],class_level=69,help_en=[[A blend of six impurities in its shell have left one soblyn even more strung out than usual. One might leave the creature to its own devices and hope that it learns to live with its pain without further endangering the lives of the smallfolk who call Loch Seld home. Or, one might just put the poor thing out of its misery and hope the Lifestream has a better plan for it next time around.]],name_ja=[[狂気の鉱虫「クレイジーソブラン」]],},[1287]={name_fr=[[Vous Ne Pondrez Point]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Eine Ist Keine, Zwei Sind Der Tod]],name=[[Par For The Course]],class_level=69,help_en=[[A hungry fisher once said, “one vepar is never enough.” Said fisher was killed on a half-full stomach by the third vepar he attempted to reel that fateful autumn morning, giving rise to the adage, “a vepar dead is another night safe in bed.”]],name_ja=[[濡れた魚]],},[1288]={name_fr=[[Cadavres Exquis]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Bis Zum Letzten Tropfen]],name=[[Sip When I'm Dead]],class_level=69,help_en=[[When kaluks cannot locate fresh lifeblood to drink, they take to the potter's fields where they probe the soil for freshly buried corpses. This, unsurprisingly, does not sit well with the relatives of the recently deceased.]],name_ja=[[死人に口なし]],},[1289]={name_fr=[[Rétention D'éther]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Ich Bin Ein Phoebad - Holt Mich Hier Raus!]],name=[[Who's Phoebad]],class_level=69,help_en=[[The salt crystals of Loch Seld make for perfect receptacles of errant aether discharge. When enough aether builds in these formations, it can give them life, but most often it is life in only the simplest sense of the word─driven by the basest of urges: sleep, hunger...murder. The phoebad do not belong on this realm. Send them back whence they came.]],name_ja=[[塩の恋人]],},[1290]={name_fr=[[Défi: Thalassina Thérapie]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Seldmonster]],name=[[Yabby Hunters]],class_level=69,help_en=[[There are those who claim the Loch Seld Monster is no more than a hoax, contrived by enterprising Ala Mhigans to dupe rich foreign emissaries into spending sacksful of coin on excursions to find the beast. There are also those who have been sliced in half by the giant yabby's claws. Those are the true believers.]],name_ja=[[純白の鉄鋏「ロッホロッホ」]],},[1291]={name_fr=[[C'est Pas Ma Guerre]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Nanka-Zanker]],name=[[Enemy Territory]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Territorial disputes amongst the diverse fauna of Loch Seld are as frequent as they are deadly, the latest featuring a school of chelone overtaking the lake bank several ninki nankas called home. Without a place to hunt and nest, the wavekin are moving towards a new territorial dispute─one between the nankas and a small fishing village.]],name_ja=[[ナンカ移動時代]],},[1292]={name_fr=[[Défi: C'est Toujours Pas Ma Guerre]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Chukwas Rache]],name=[[One Bad Mother Chukwa]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Weakened by the epic battle that resulted in a large swathe of loch nanka territory being claimed by her school of chelone, murderous High Matron Chukwa is at her most vulnerable. If there is to be any chance of slaying this most foul of lake-beasts, it is now.]],name_ja=[[白き侵略者「チュクワ」]],},[1293]={name_fr=[[Papillonnez En Paix]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Bienen Und Blumen Und Saprias]],name=[[Give Bees A Chance]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Farmers of the Lochs look to the region's many bees and butterflies to help pollinate their meager crops. Sapria look to those same creatures to fill their fathomless bellies. As a sapria is not that satisfying in a salad, the smallfolk have asked that you save the bees instead.]],name_ja=[[花粉戦争]],},[1294]={name_fr=[[Mimétisme Royal]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Königin Edilas Vermächtnis]],name=[[About Face]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Named for the queen who saw to the construction of the gardens in which it now resides, Creeping Edila is said even to resemble Her Most Royal Highness, albeit before she made her face in the morning.]],name_ja=[[草の女王]],},[1295]={name_fr=[[Défi: Que Serra Serra?]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Vorsicht, Bissig]],name=[[No Time Is A Good Time]],class_level=69,help_en=[[With serrated teeth strong enough to rip apart even twice-plated Garlean warmachina, Serra is a force of nature not to be reckoned with lightly. Only those who favor unlasting glory over near-certain death need test their fortune in a battle of wits with this wavekin.]],name_ja=[[塩湖の金鋸「セラ」]],},[1296]={name_fr=[[Tu Casses, Tu Répares]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Stier Mich Nicht An!]],name=[[Mazeless Runner]],class_level=69,help_en=[[A minotaur without a labyrinth is like a dog without a bone─prone to wanton killing sprees that most often end in the annihilation of entire villages. In other words, nothing like a dog without a bone. Slay the minotaurs. Prevent annihilation.]],name_ja=[[ミノタウロスのお皿]],},[1297]={name_fr=[[La Garde Meurt, Mais Ne Se Rend Pas Compte Qu'elle Est Morte]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Grab Der Könige]],name=[[Kingsgrave]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Ancient Ala Mhigan kings believed even after they died, the spirits of fallen enemies would harry them far into the afterlife. To combat this, they had their honor guard buried with them...whether they were dead at the time of the regent's passing or not. Several of those spirits, not overly pleased with the fates thrust upon them, still roam the land with vengeance in their hearts.]],name_ja=[[キングズガード]],},[1298]={name_fr=[[Butinez En Paix]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Schmetterlingseffekt]],name=[[Fate No Morpho]],class_level=69,help_en=[[A scholar once claimed that a butterfly flapping its wings in Gyr Abania gave rise to the storms that rocked Othard's eastern shores. If that were true, the amount of flapping caused by the royal morphos trying in vain to escape the gaping maws of hungry abaddons will see Doma under ten yalms of rain by moon's end. Just in case, you may want to slay those abaddons.]],name_ja=[[バタフライエフェクト]],},[1299]={name_fr=[[Développement Dhara-ble]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Senklochsauger]],name=[[I Can Feel The Earth Move]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Dhara feed by draining the soil of its earth-aspected aether, leaving the land brittle and prone to erosion. To prevent deadly sinkholes and landslides, the dhara must be dealt with.]],name_ja=[[ミリオンダラ・ソルティ]],},[1300]={name_fr=[[Sangsues Sans Frontières]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Mit Kind Und Egel]],name=[[To Leech His Own]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Unable to bear the thought of his beloved leeches being disposed of by the Empire, the royal physicker liberated his blood-loving assistants on the night of the invasion by tossing them into the privy where they eventually swam their way out into Loch Seld. And there, for the past three decades, have the wavekin thrived, growing fat on the blood of hapless travelers and foolish children.]],name_ja=[[薬用リーチ]],},[1301]={name_fr=[[Défi: Un Petit Pas Pour Le Colosse]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Wandelnde Erdbeben]],name=[[Tellus A Tale]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Where Tellus walks, the ground moves─or so sayeth those who swear that the region's recurrent tremors are not, as scholars claim, movements of the land's crust atop rivers of molten rock, but in fact the lumbering gait of a modern-day giant.]],name_ja=[[動く震源地「テルース」]],},[1302]={name_fr=[[L'argile Est Agile]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Nachwehen Der Katastrophe]],name=[[OK, Golem]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Though the Eorzean Alliance has claimed the Seventh Umbral Era concluded, there are still parts of the realm which suffer the lasting effects of Dalamud's fall. One such area can be found in the mountains circling Loch Seld where aetherial instability engenders mindless golems.]],name_ja=[[マウンテン]],},[1303]={name_fr=[[L'affliction D'Anselot]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Respektlose Gäste]],name=[[Ancelot's Fear]],class_level=69,help_en=[[The Empire's outlawing of religion in Ala Mhigo has seen sacred sites fall into ruin, those once tasked with their upkeep forced to abandon all labors of faith. As a result, locations such as the royal crypts are now overrun with creatures threatening to defile thousands of years of history.]],name_ja=[[アンセロットの嘆き]],},[1304]={name_fr=[[La Hantise D'Anselot]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Verirrte Schatten]],name=[[Ancelot's Folly]],class_level=69,help_en=[[The chants of ceremonies that once assured that restless spirits remained beyond the corporeal realm no longer echo through the royal crypts, allowing specters and ghosts to return to the world of the living unmolested. If allowed to escape the palace halls, it will be but a matter of time before they descend upon the Loch's villages.]],name_ja=[[アンセロットの恐れ]],},[1305]={name_fr=[[La Dernière Volonté D'Anselot]],class_level_max=70,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Auferstehung Des Königs]],name=[[Ancelot's Finale]],class_level=69,help_en=[[Unaware of his own death, King Manfred has risen from his tomb to rule once again─or so that is what the evil spirit possessing the rotting corpse of the long-deceased regent wants you to believe.]],name_ja=[[アンセロットの願い]],},[1306]={name_fr=[[Sur La Route Des Dataq]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Nomaden]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Departures]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Having taken from the land all they dare, the Dataqi tribe has broken camp and begun their exodus to a new home. However, not but a few bells from their departure do they spy a cloud of buzzflies─an ill omen whose arrival may spell extreme hardship in the moons to come. Perhaps if the vilekin were slain, the tribe's fortune may yet be preserved.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：バズフライ遭遇]],},[1307]={name_fr=[[Toujours Dataq]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Raubtiere]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Distractions]],class_level=65,help_en=[[As the Dataqi search for a new home, they are hounded every step by literal hounds─steppe gedan who seem intent on following the tribespeople at a distance until their guards are dropped and their bellies exposed.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：ガーダン襲撃]],},[1308]={name_fr=[[La Première Traite N'attend Pas]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Schafsmilch]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Duty]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Finally settled in their new home, the Dataqi have returned to their daily routines─one such task being the milking of the sheep. The livestock, however, remain ill at ease in these unfamiliar surroundings, and the tribe's milkmaid seeks assistance in filling the jugs.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：羊乳搾り]],},[1309]={name_fr=[[Une Faim De Berger]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Dzo-Jagd]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Deprivation]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Their rations depleted from the long journey, the Dataqi seek to replenish their supply tents. A herd of wild dzos was spotted near the camp, and its meat could feed the tribe for days─moons, even, if the flesh is jerked.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：ケナガウシ狩り]],},[1310]={name_fr=[[Le Retour Du Gedan]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Ausgehungert]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Deterrence]],class_level=65,help_en=[[The Azim Steppe has no shortage of starving hounds, and despite having driven off an entire pack during their last exodus, the Dataqi find themselves surrounded by even more steppe gedan─these even more hungry than the last.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：ガーダン再襲撃]],},[1311]={name_fr=[[Je Veux Tes Vêtements, Tes Bottes Et Ton Outre D'aïrag!]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Ugund-Räuber]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Desperation]],class_level=65,help_en=[[A band of Ugundi warriors drunk on fermented goat milk have begun a charge on the Dataqi camp that, at best, could be called reckless. Still, a reckless charge can at any time turn deadly if not prepared. Send the sotted sods back to the steppe that they may sleep this all off.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：ウグンド強襲]],},[1312]={name_fr=[[Compagnons D'infortune]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Mammuts]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Distress]],class_level=65,help_en=[[The tribe has come across a hunter in dire need of aid, having bitten off far more than she can chew in her ill-fated attempt to bring down a mammoth by herself.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：狩人救出]],},[1313]={name_fr=[[Chasse Préventive]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Herdenschutz]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Displacement]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Any time a new camp is built, the first and foremost task is to clear the area of any wildlife that might pose a threat to the tribe's livestock. To secure this particular location, a pack of gulo gulo must be dealt with swiftly and cleanly, as not to attract any further predators.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：グログロ討伐]],},[1315]={name_fr=[[Un Voisin Qui Trompe énormément]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Matanga]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Diplomacy]],class_level=65,help_en=[[As if to say “you are not welcome here,” Matanga have descended upon the Dataqi settlement, bent on tearing each and every tent to shreds. It may be time to strike camp and move on, but before doing so, the current threat must be quelled.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：マタンガ強襲]],},[1316]={name_fr=[[Rancune D'éléphant]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Blutrache]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Decimation]],class_level=65,help_en=[[The slaughter of their brethren has sent the remaining Matanga into a fit of unbridled fury. No longer content with driving the Dataqi people from their territory, the Matanga now seek the death of the tribe's every last man, woman, and child.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：マタンガ遭遇]],},[1318]={name_fr=[[Dataq, Goro, Même Combat]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Verbündete]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Divergence]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Sounds of fighting in the distance compel the Dataqi nomads to stop and scout ahead, where they find a band of Goro warriors in a heated battle with a party of savage Matanga. Join the scouts in aiding the Goro in their plight.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：ゴロ族救出]],},[1319]={name_fr=[[On Prend Les Matangas Et On Recommence]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Unerbittlich]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Declarations]],class_level=65,help_en=[[Not ones to forgive or forget, a Matanga war party seeking vengeance for their fallen brothers has emerged from the steppe, weapons drawn. There will be no surrender, only death. To which party is yet to be decided.]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：マタンガ逆襲]],},[1320]={name_fr=[[Le Roi Des Matangas]],class_level_max=69,patch={number=[[4.0]],},name_de=[[Das Leben Der Dataq: Anjana]],name=[[The Dataqi Chronicles: Dominion]],class_level=65,help_en=[[In a final act of desperation, the crestfallen Matanga plead to their almighty regent, Anjana, for one last boon─to descend from the heavens and vanquish the Dataqi and Goro tribes once and for all. The true trial of the steppe begins...and ends...here!]],name_ja=[[ダタクの旅：大王出陣]],},[1321]={name_fr=[[Y A Du Soleil Et Des Pieuvres]],class_level_max=35,patch={number=[[4.05]],},name_de=[[Tag Der Tentakel]],name=[[The Summer Of Ultros]],class_level=30,help_en=[[The beautiful female faire-goers are under attack by the lewd Ultros and his uncontrollable tentacles. Fight the fiend off to defend their honor.]],name_ja=[[紅蓮祭「襲来 オルトロス！」]],},[1322]={name_fr=[[Punir L'infâme Marchand]],class_level_max=35,patch={number=[[4.05]],},name_de=[[Über Den Fisch Gezogen]],name=[[To Bait A Baiter]],class_level=30,help_en=[[A merchant of deplorable morals is attempting to sell his bait at an outlandish price. Defeat the merchant's bodyguards to defend the fair market.]],name_ja=[[紅蓮祭「法外な釣り餌」]],},[1323]={name_fr=[[Coquillages Et Cisailleurs]],class_level_max=35,patch={number=[[4.05]],},name_de=[[Grillpartysprenger]],name=[[Snippers Gonna Snip]],class_level=30,help_en=[[A hungry pack of snippers has caught the scent of a delivery of fish bound for the faire kitchens. Protect the fish crates from the Moonfire snippers, so that faire-goers can indulge in the bounty of the sea.]],name_ja=[[紅蓮祭「魚狙いの蟹退治」]],},[1324]={name_fr=[[Ah, Ces Touristes...]],class_level_max=35,patch={number=[[4.05]],},name_de=[[Unser Strand Muss Schöner Werden]],name=[[Adopt A Beach]],class_level=30,help_en=[[Refuse left by faire-goers has ruined the scenic beaches of the isle. Gather the Moonfire Faire rubbish and deliver it to the faire chaperone.]],name_ja=[[紅蓮祭「常夏の大掃除」]],},[1325]={name_fr=[[De Tréants à Truands]],class_level_max=16,patch={number=[[4.1]],},name_de=[[Knorrige Diebe]],name=[[Bad Luck Comes In Trees]],class_level=11,help_en=[[The thieving treants must be stopped without damaging the decorations. Pepper them with starbursts to force them into submission.]],name_ja=[[星芒祭「森の盗人」]],},[1328]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'empereur Des Bourrasques]],class_level_max=7,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Herr Kaiser]],name=[[The Swarm Never Sets]],class_level=4,help_en=[[More than twice the size of a Hyur male and at least as pestilent, the Emperor of Anemos has arrived to defend his empire against encroaching adventurers. The murderous look in his compound eyes will soon suppress any guilt you feel over this entirely avoidable situation.]],name_ja=[[疾風の帝王「アネモス・エンペラー」]],},[1329]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Démon Des Tempêtes]],class_level_max=23,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Ein Windiger Kerl]],name=[[Wail In The Willows]],class_level=20,help_en=[[The wind howls with voices of those long dead, heralding the advent of the high voidsent, Pazuzu. Weather the winds he wields, lest your own screaming soul be added to the chorus.]],name_ja=[[暴風の魔王「パズズ」]],},[1330]={name_fr=[[Les Concerts De Rue Des Églantines]],class_level_max=255,patch={number=[[4.2]],},name_de=[[Die Drosseln Rocken Den Kreuzgang]],name=[[Color My World]],class_level=5,help_en=[[The Songbirds have taken the stage! Speak with the royal handmaiden to get dressed and join the show!]],name_ja=[[プリンセスデー「三歌姫の路上公演」]],},[1331]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Dragon Démentiel]],class_level_max=20,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Schlafende Drachen Soll Man Nicht Wecken]],name=[[Wine And Honey]],class_level=17,help_en=[[As the old saying goes: every wyrm's ending is just a voidsent wyrm's beginning. Banish this particularly vicious example, and remember that no one's to blame—except the adventurers that killed the high dragon whose dying breath summoned forth this monstrosity.]],name_ja=[[狂乱の暗竜「ファヴニル」]],},[1332]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Fleur D'Eurêka]],class_level_max=4,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Schmerzvoller Hüftschwung]],name=[[Unsafety Dance]],class_level=1,help_en=[[Scattered flower petals adrift on the wind may calm the mind and soothe the soul, but being showered with needles detracts from the experience. Best halt Sabotender Corrido's frenzied dance before someone loses an eye.]],name_ja=[[舞踏の大花「サボテンダー・コリード」]],},[1333]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'ultime Soupir De La Beauté]],class_level_max=6,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Zurück Zu Den Toten]],name=[[Teles House]],class_level=3,help_en=[[Thought to have abandoned the realm for more accommodating climes, imagine the surprise of the expeditionaries surveying Eureka when they found themselves halfway down the gullet of the legendary (killer) songbird, Teles.]],name_ja=[[最後の美声「テレス」]],},[1334]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Dévoreur]],class_level_max=11,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Ich Will So Bleiben Wie Ich Bin]],name=[[Prove Your Amemettle]],class_level=8,help_en=[[Amemet knows that one doesn't become an apex predator by being selective about his meals. He devours any creature that he can bite, tear, or bludgeon to death, including other carnivorous dinosaurs, and is now poised to eat Eureka out of island and ecosystem.]],name_ja=[[貪り喰らう者「アミメット」]],},[1335]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Bête Humaine]],class_level_max=12,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Gerippeimpfung Empfohlen]],name=[[Caym What May]],class_level=9,help_en=[[Slaying a massive carnivorous scalekin may seem the end of one's troubles, while in fact, it is just the beginning. That corpse left rotting in the forest is the perfect means for an aether-starved voidsent to worm its way into our realm...and start killing again.]],name_ja=[[獣脚の怪人「カイム」]],},[1336]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Sage Putréfié]],class_level_max=13,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Den Ball Halte Flach, Den Witz Lieber Nicht]],name=[[The Killing Of A Sacred Bombadier]],class_level=10,help_en=[[Hyperbole can be employed to suggest that the stench of rotting goobbue seven days dead is enough to kill a man. If that rotting goobbue, however, is being used as a vessel for a voracious voidsent host, then the need for hyperbole is no more.]],name_ja=[[腐臭の賢者「ボンバディール」]],},[1337]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Géant Légendaire]],class_level_max=17,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Große Probleme Auf Kleiner Insel]],name=[[Sing, Muse]],class_level=14,help_en=[[Polyphemus is proof positive that fame and an enlarged cranium need not go together. Be that as it may, his large torso, large club, and large dinner parties (which only occasionally end with him devouring the guests, but are always terrible) are reason enough to extend him no hospitality.]],name_ja=[[高名なる巨人「ポリュペモス」]],},[1338]={name_fr=[[Défi: La Reine Infernale]],class_level_max=22,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Ein Königreich Für Kein Lama]],name=[[Drama Lamashtu]],class_level=19,help_en=[[The hells have no fury like a woman scorned. They are, however, home to many a dead woman scorned, whose fury is possibly worse. The voidsent queen Lamashtu would know, since she's the bloodsucking demon who killed them all.]],name_ja=[[魔の王妃「ラマシュトゥ」]],},[1339]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Scorpion Mythique]],class_level_max=14,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Wütend Wie Ein Hurrikan]],name=[[Short Serket 2]],class_level=11,help_en=[[There is nothing worse than a marsh teeming with thousands of scuttling scorpions...except a marsh teeming with thousands of scuttling scorpions and their giant queen.]],name_ja=[[幻の魔蠍「セルケト」]],},[1340]={name_fr=[[Défi: L'insatiable Cerbère]],class_level_max=21,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Widerlegte Weisheit]],name=[[I Amarok]],class_level=18,help_en=[[When commanding an army of voidsent abominations on a campaign to quell a world of its light, two heads are always better than one. Luckily for Amarok─dread wolf of the deepvoid─he has three.]],name_ja=[[異界の魔犬「アマロック」]],},[1341]={name_fr=[[Défi: Douche Froide Pour Le Hazmat Roi]],class_level_max=19,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Heizkostenreduzierung]],name=[[To The Mat]],class_level=16,help_en=[[Once known to his loyal subjects as King of the Flame, for years Hazmat has wallowed in the lightless void, unable to wield his brilliant, fiery magicks. Now, unbound from the darkness, the self-proclaimed regent is free to set the world alight...literally.]],name_ja=[[燃える大王「キング・ハズマット」]],},[1342]={name_fr=[[Défi: Colère Aviaire]],class_level_max=18,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Futterneid]],name=[[Simurghasbord]],class_level=15,help_en=[[After its avian prey was snatched right out of its beak, this ravening predator began a merciless hunt for anything—or anyone—it might carry away and devour. Proceed with caution, as surely a fowl foul enough to cannibalize other birds would have no qualms about downing a Lalafell or two.]],name_ja=[[憤怒の怪鳥「シームルグ・ストライダー」]],},[1343]={name_fr=[[Défi: On M'appelle Le Cavalier Blanc]],class_level_max=16,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Kopflos]],name=[[When You Ride Alone]],class_level=13,help_en=[[Don't be fooled by his choice of attire. Come from the void to aid his hungry brethren in their quest to consume this realm's aether, the White Rider is a deadly beacon for the forces of darkness.]],name_ja=[[勝利の騎士「ホワイトライダー」]],},[1344]={name_fr=[[Défi: Un Cadavre Tout Sauf Exquis]],class_level_max=8,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Ränkeschmiede]],name=[[One Missed Callisto]],class_level=5,help_en=[[If a bear falls victim to mind-controlling spores in the woods, does it make a sound? Judging by the bestial roars echoing across the isle each night, the correct answer would be “yes.”]],name_ja=[[蠢く死体「カリスト」]],},[1345]={name_fr=[[Défi: Tempête Sur Eurêka]],class_level_max=10,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Raus Aus Meinem Revier]],name=[[Disinherit The Wind]],class_level=7,help_en=[[One might imagine wind spirits as gentle, if capricious, wanderers. The best cure for such delusions is to witness the wildly territorial Jahannam's overblown reaction to the disruption of wind currents encircling its domain.]],name_ja=[[強風の妖精「ジャハンナム」]],},[1346]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Jugement De Julika]],class_level_max=15,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Vernichtendes Unkraut]],name=[[Don't Judge Me, Morbol]],class_level=12,help_en=[[Upon discovering her seedbeds rendered barren by man's savage sickles, Julika─ancient tangle of root and vine─has sworn vengeance on those who would dare slash her spawn. And her first step? To reseed the earth with a new army of loyal sprouts.]],name_ja=[[種まき「ジャッジメンタル・ジュリカ」]],},[1347]={name_fr=[[Défi: Régler Son Compte à Number]],class_level_max=9,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Zahlenmäßige Überlegenheit]],name=[[By Numbers]],class_level=6,help_en=[[A wicked puppetmaster's abrupt disappearance from this plane has left his insentient servant free to wreak whatever havoc its mechanical mind can muster.]],name_ja=[[主なき人形「ナンバーズ」]],},[1348]={name_fr=[[Défi: Le Seigneur De La Terre Interdite]],class_level_max=5,patch={number=[[4.25]],},name_de=[[Küssen Verboten]],name=[[The Shadow Over Anemos]],class_level=2,help_en=[[For all that we know of him, the Lord of Anemos may seek simply to protect his subjects. Alas, his ever-gaping maw reveals no secrets, only impossibly sharp teeth. However noble his intentions, he is a threat as great as any other when he approaches with undulating tentacles aloft.]],name_ja=[[大蛸の王者「ロード・オブ・アネモス」]],},[1349]={name_fr=[[Les Concerts De Rue Des Églantines]],class_level_max=255,patch={number=[[4.2]],},name_de=[[Die Drosseln Rocken Den Kreuzgang]],name=[[Color My World]],class_level=5,help_en=[[The Songbirds have taken the stage! Speak with the royal handmaiden to get dressed and join the show!]],name_ja=[[プリンセスデー「三歌姫の路上公演」]],},[1350]={name_fr=[[Les Concerts De Rue Des Églantines]],class_level_max=255,patch={number=[[4.2]],},name_de=[[Die Drosseln Rocken Den Kreuzgang]],name=[[Color My World]],class_level=5,help_en=[[The Songbirds have taken the stage! Speak with the royal handmaiden to get dressed and join the show!]],name_ja=[[プリンセスデー「三歌姫の路上公演」]],},},index={["Clever Girls"]=120,["One Enchanted Eve"]=121,["Sprig Cleaning"]=122,["Something In The Water"]=123,["The Sting"]=124,["Asipatra Attacks"]=125,["Leader Of The Pack"]=126,["A Mother Scorned"]=127,["Alux Of The Draw"]=128,["エバーシェイドの収穫祭"]=130,["Lethe On My Mind"]=131,["Training Day"]=136,["Bleeding Green"]=137,["Tastes Like Chick"]=138,["Sleep Tight"]=139,["Spirithold Run"]=140,["Love Is In The Air"]=141,["There's Something About Lou"]=142,["Now I See Bees I Won"]=143,["Royal Rumble"]=144,["戦場までは何マルム？"]=145,["What A Bee Wants"]=148,["Stopping The Spread"]=149,["Jack Of All Trades"]=150,["リトルブリッジの戦い"]=151,["Protecting The Patch"]=152,["The Hunted"]=153,["Eft For Dead"]=154,["The Negotiators"]=158,["Breaching The Hive"]=159,["Clearing The Hive"]=160,["Defending The Hive"]=161,["Keeping The Hive"]=162,["Kickin' It With The Kedtraps"]=163,["The Coeurl King"]=164,["Another Round"]=166,["Stag Parting"]=167,